title: cherry jubilee
directions: Fill a tall glass with lots of ice.
Stir the orange juice, cherry juice and ginger ale or Fresca.
Add the cherries for garnish.
Yields 1 serving.

title: lemon velvet pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes at low speed, then 7 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until center of cake gives indication of being done.

title: sheilah's favorite french onion soup
directions: Melt in a large pot the butter and saute sliced onions until golden.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, flour and a dash of pepper.
Add water and beef consomme.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add sherry.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in a small amount of boiling, salted water in saucepan for 10 minutes or until wilted; drain well.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in wedges.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix beef, onions and rice together and arrange between wedges. Combine water, tomatoes and seasonings and pour over casserole. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Heat milk nearly to boiling.
Stir in cornmeal gradually and cook until consistency of mush (fairly thick but not stiff), stirring constantly.
Add baking powder, salt and egg yolks, beaten until light.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
(I simply put a blob of Crisco in a casserole and place in oven to melt.) Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serve at once with plenty of butter from the casserole in which it was baked.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Beat the cream cheese and confectioners sugar with a small amount of milk. Combine 2 envelopes Dream Whip with 1 cup of milk. Whip until stiff.
Mix with cream cheese and sugar mixture. Thicken the strawberries with a little bit of cornstarch.
Bake an angel food cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan. Take the cake out of the pan and cut through the middle.
Place half the cake back in pan and spread cream cheese and strawberries.
Put the other layer of cake on top and use rest of cheese mixture and strawberries. Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut and cook chicken and place in 7 x 11-inch buttered dish. Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Crush crackers and mix with poppy seed. Put on top. Melt oleo and pour over. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Serves 12 to 16.

title: nancy's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Blend in pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into 7 x 11-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Blend sour cream, softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over salad.
Chill.
Makes 18 or more servings.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Slowly stir in milk. Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Blend small amount into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture. Cook and stir until thick.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Cover and cool.
Fold in 1 cup sour cream and top with no-fail meringue.

title: blue cheese dressing deluxe
directions: Combine all ingredients, then add buttermilk and sour cream. Mix well.
Store in refrigerator in covered jar.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Cook in double boiler and simmer about 1 hour.
Just before serving, add about 1/2 cup sherry wine.
Serves 8.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Make sauce from oleo, flour, milk and Velveeta.
Add chilies.
Soften tortillas in sauce.
Roll beef in tortillas.
Pour rest of sauce over enchiladas.
Top with grated cheese and onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Wonderful doubled and freeze second casserole.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in skin until fork goes through.
When slightly warm, peel and slice.
Add chopped onion and let sit on top (while still warm).

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in water 30 minutes.
Cream sugar, eggs and butter and add orange juice.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Drain apricots and add to batter.
Pour into a greased and floured pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake in 350° oven 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.
Slice and spread with lite cream cheese.

title: spiced pork saute
directions: In skillet, heat oil over high heat.
On plate, mix flour with seasonings; add pork.
Toss.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Precook macaroni; drain.
Bring milk to a boil and add to macaroni plus cheese, bread and egg yolks.
Beat and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven french toast
directions: Grease as 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into 1-inch slices and arrange in one layer in bottom of dish.
In bowl, beat eggs with remaining ingredients, except margarine.
When mixed, pour over bread in dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 4 to 36 hours.
To bake, uncover, dot bread with 2 tablespoons of margarine and put pan in oven.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until bread is puffy and lightly brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Put the chopped peanuts in a separate serving bowl.
Slice apples.
Either dip or spoon some mixture on a slice of apple, then dip or spoon some nuts on top of mixture.
If apples are sliced ahead of time, coat with lemon juice to help prevent browning.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside. Cream the butter, brown sugar replacement, Equal, vanilla, applesauce, water and eggs.
Add the flour mixture and blend well. Stir in the chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Great for diabetics!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Combine all other ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix well and add 1 cup coconut.
Make into 1 large or 2 medium balls.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serve with small crackers.

title: sliced peach mold
directions: Drain both cans of fruit well.
Measure 2 cups of peach juice; add water or pineapple juice if needed for the amount.
Heat juice to boiling; add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Let cool while you cut each pineapple slice in half and arrange in Pyrex 12 x 18-inch casserole.
Make 15 servings, 3 across and 5 down.
Pit and cut peaches in 15 portions; place on top of pineapple.
Carefully add ginger ale to Jell-O and ease some of the Jell-O onto the fruit, just enough to anchor it.
Let sit in refrigerator.
Add rest of Jell-O; return to refrigerator and let set overnight.

title: caramels
directions: Mix thoroughly; stir constantly with a wooden spoon on medium to slow fire.
Cook to hard ball stage or so you can chew it.
Add nuts if desired and vanilla and pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Let cool.
Cut into strips and then into pieces and wrap with wax paper.
Takes about 25 minutes of cooking time.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: Make a white sauce from the butter, flour, milk and grated cheese.
Cook the remaining ingredients 10 minutes or until done. Add the white sauce and heat together.

title: quick chicken divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Layer chicken over broccoli.
In small bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; mix well.
Spread over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: picadilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Scald milk and melt shortening. Stir all ingredients together.
Add 6 to 7 cups flour and knead well. Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch dough down and make into loaves. Let rise again. Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place cut side down in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Saute onions with butter.
Add remaining ingredients and stuff into squash.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more until cheese melts.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Saute garlic in oil for one minute, add carrots, onions and celery and saute for 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth, potatoes, noodles and chicken.
Cook until done.
Add milk.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Dissolve first three items together.
Add milk.
Pour into ice cube tray and freeze until just edges are beginning to form crystals.
Remove from freezer and beat until stiff.
Replace in freezer.

title: vince early's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage, drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours. Serve with grated cheese and crackers.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and 1 (8 ounce) butter or margarine. Press in buttered pan.
Mix powdered sugar, 2 eggs and 8 ounce cream cheese.
Pour on top of cake.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven or until middle is done.
Sprinkle cake top with powdered sugar.

title: marcus grey's breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Butter bread & arrange in a greased 13x9 inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage and drain well.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt & pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover & chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vinegar to eggs.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes at 325° to 350° or until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: chocolate praline cake with broiled icing
directions: In a small saucepan, warm buttermilk and butter, do not scald. Pour liquid into a mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and slowly add to mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: forever amber
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in baking dish or pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until beginning to brown on top.
Let cool.
Then spoon out in bite sizes and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and oleo.
Add sugar and eggs. Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: girl scout cookie pie
directions: Crush a box of Girl Scout mint cookies.
Put 2/3 of crushed cookies in bottom of pie pan.
In double boiler, melt marshmallows and milk.
Add creme de menthe.
Let cook while whipping cream. Fold hot mixture into whipped cream.
Pour over crushed cookies. Sprinkle rest of crushed cookies on top and refrigerate or freeze. Serve chilled.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover with foil.
Store in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Make into rolls and let rise about 1 to 1 1/2 hours covered on countertop with towel.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir well.
Add buttermilk; mix well. Stir in raisins.
Spoon in three well-greased No.
303 (1 pound) tin cans.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool; remove from cans and slice to serve.
Refrigerate rest in plastic bags.
Good with baked beans, hearty soups, salads or use in sandwiches.
Also makes good gift.

title: caldo
directions: Boil first four ingredients together.
Add enough water to keep covered.
Cook until meat is tender (approximately 2 hours). During last 1/2 hour of cooking add sliced carrots.
About 10 minutes later, add corn on the cob. Then during the last 10 minutes add sliced zucchini and cabbage.
Serve in bowls.
Add fresh lime to each serving.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate, cool. Add remaining ingredients to eggs. Add cooled chocolate. Pour into greased 8 X 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: red cucumber rings
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Slice and remove seeds.
Mix lime and water. Pour over rings.
Let set 24 hours.
Drain off lime water and wash in clear water.
Cover with cold water and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain off water.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Cream lightly shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour boiling water over.
Add cold water.
Dissolve yeast in a little warm water. Add well beaten eggs and yeast, then add flour and mix thoroughly. Butter a large bowl.
Put dough in it.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out and cut in small pieces.
Cut pieces like pie pieces.
Roll up starting from large end, finishing up with small end.
Roll and make 2 hours before cooking.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Melt butter and spread over rolls when done.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together until foamy.
Add sugar and vanilla and continue to beat.
Add apples and beat slightly; set aside. Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add raisins to flour mixture.
Combine with egg mixture.
Beat slightly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple until pudding is dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot fruit
directions: Arrange fruit in dish. Pour margarine mixture over fruit and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mash potatoes and add all ingredients. Grease and flour 13 x 9 inch pan. Spread mixture 1 inch thick in pan. Cook until brown at 350° to 375°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Thaw the spinach out and then squeeze juice out.
Serve.

title: parmesan chicken(serves 2)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour and Parmesan with salt and pepper and dredge the breasts, pressing the cheese into the chicken.
Saute the chicken and garlic in the olive oil over medium heat until browned.
Transfer the chicken to an ovenproof casserole.
Deglaze the skillet with the wine and pour over the chicken.
Sprinkle the additional Parmesan over the chicken and bake for 30 minutes.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Cook beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown. Drain. Stir in soup & milk. Stir baking mix and water in baking dish until moistened. Spread evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread beef mixture over batter, sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: butter "cut-out" cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put baking powder in flour and slowly add flour mix to creamed mix.
Chill dough several hours before rolling and cutting cookies (chill overnight if you desire).
Bake at 350° approximately 7 minutes or until edges are brown.
Frost with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: quiche
directions: In a large bowl, beat the eggs well.
Beat in the milk, salt, pepper, basil and nutmeg.
Fold in the grated cheese and ham. Pour the mixture into the pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated vegetable platter
directions: Whisk together thoroughly the vinegar and oil.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt and garlic powder; continue to whisk. Fold in egg and chives.
Use vegetables listed or any other vegetables desired.
Arrange drained vegetables separately in a large dish; do not mix them.
Pour marinade over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: easy lemon sauce
directions: Follow directions for pudding, using 1/2 cup more liquid. Serve hot over homemade gingerbread squares.
May spruce up with chopped nuts or chopped celery.

title: katie's wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare wild rice to package directions.
Brown sausage and drain; add onion, green pepper and celery.
Add soups, cheese, mushroom pieces and rice.
Mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: taco dip
directions: Follow taco package instructions and add 1/2 can refried beans.
Layer hamburg mixture, salsa, cheese, tomatoes, lettuce, olives and onions.
Top with sour cream.
Serve warm with nachos.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel on crust; sprinkle with pecans and refrigerate. Stir pudding and milk constantly over medium heat until it reaches a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into crust.
Place plastic on surface.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Remove plastic.
Garnish with Cool Whip and additional caramel topping.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and set aside.
Mash avocados.
Mix with lemon juice, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Layer over beans.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spread this mixture over 2nd layer.
Sprinkle chopped green onions.
Sprinkle chopped black olives.
Sprinkle grated cheese.
Sprinkle chopped tomatoes on top. Picante sauce may be spooned and jalapeno peppers on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel nut slices
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in.
Add nuts.
Use wax paper to shape dough into 2 rolls 2 inches across.
Chill.
Heat oven to 400°. Slice dough 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen.
Dough keeps in refrigerator several weeks.
Slice when needed.

title: spaghetti squash and fruit salad
directions: Cut spaghetti squash in half lengthwise.
Take out seeds. Place squash face down in baking pan with small amount of water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until semi-soft.
Allow to cool in refrigerator overnight.
Scoop out pulp and put into bowl.

title: peanut butter "tandy cake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cream butter with 1 cup sugar.
Add egg, milk and 1/4 teaspoon extract.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Blend into butter mixture. Cover dough and refrigerate at least 25 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously butter 14-inch round pizza pan. Press dough evenly into pan.
Bake until lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool crust in pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook ground beef and drain fat.
Add the corn, tomatoes, onion, butter, salt, chili powder and garlic and cook 15 minutes; remove from heat.
Mix the milk, egg and corn meal well; pour into buttered casserole over first mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Note:
I usually put 3 to 4 tablespoons of jalapeno Cheez Whiz.

title: pepperidge farm party rolls
directions: Cut rolls and make sandwiches with ham and cheese.
Melt margarine and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over sandwiches. Heat in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Cool for at least 1 hour.

title: pizza cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
In medium bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour and baking soda until well blended.
Spread dough into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle marshmallows and candies on cookie during the last 5 minutes of baking.
Cool 10 minutes in pan on wire rack.
To serve, cut cookies into 16 wedges. (Use your imagination, adding more candies, etc.)

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugars and egg.
Cream.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to Crisco mixture.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon and sugar (1 teaspoon cinnamon to 2 tablespoons sugar).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips, add milk, stirring constantly until milk and chocolate blends.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Line 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish with waxed paper.
Pour fudge into dish and place in refrigerator until firm.
Then cut into squares.

title: braciola
directions: Butterfly steak.
Spread parsley and garlic over it.
Cover it with alternate strips of sopressata and cheese.
Roll and tie with string.
Saute in oil, turning to brown all around.
Pour in tomato sauce, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
If sauce is too acid, add some sugar.
Simmer until meat feels tender when pierced with fork.

title: mach lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and add spaghetti sauce. Cook noodles and drain. Add to meat sauce.
Spread half of the meat
and noodles in a long cake pan.
Spread 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese over mixture. Add the rest of the meat mixture.
Spread 2 cups of shredded Cheddar cheese.
Layer the top with sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Put in a 350° oven until cheese melts.
Let sit 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: candi's coffee cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and rest of ingredients.
Pour half batter in greased angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of topping over batter and spread rest of batter over, then the remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, green pepper and carrots.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage.

title: amanda's favorite pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cook on a hot, greased griddle.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° for glass pan).
In pan, heat soup, broth, chicken and vegetables to boiling, stirring constantly. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over soup mixture (crust will rise during baking).
Bake 30 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Combine sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples. Combine flour, brown sugar, oats, baking powder, nutmeg and remaining cinnamon. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until apples are tender. Yield: 12 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes with parsley
directions: Arrange half the potatoes in a well buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the onion and half the parsley.
Arrange remaining potatoes, onion and parsley as a second layer.
In saucepan, heat butter and add garlic.
Saute 1 minute or until garlic releases its flavor (you can smell it).
Blend milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Pour into pan with butter and garlic.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Pour over potatoes in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, if baking along with a roast.
Garnish with parsley.

title: wheat germ apple crisp
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place apples in casserole.
In medium bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot and place in a 350° oven. Bake for 3 hours, stirring twice.

title: peach cobbler (or any fruit)
directions: Melt margarine. Pour into cooking dish (9 x 9). Mix flour, sugar and milk to a smooth batter. Pour over margarine. Don't stir. Add fruit and juice. Don't stir. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cranberry juice and thawed lemonade in a punch bowl.
Pour in club soda.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: gayle's chicken souse
directions: Marinate chicken in sour and salt and pepper for 1/2 hour. Pour enough water to barely cover chicken.	Cook for 20 minutes. Add Allspice.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook for 20 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are done.
Just before done, add fresh basil or dried tarragon.

title: frozen frappuccino(similar to starbucks)
directions: Combine coffee, milk, sugar, chocolate syrup, and salt in a blender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Mix chicken, soups and milk together.
Fold in prepared stuffing.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and brown.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Make
white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Stir in sour cream
and Cheez Whiz.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Arrange eggs in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour sauce over eggs.
Top with bacon.
Bake, covered, at 350°, until bubbly.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Gradually add sugar to margarine creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and preserves.
Sift together dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture, mixing thoroughly. Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until cookies are delicately browned.

title: salade d'endives
directions: Make a vinaigrette dressing, using oil, cider vinegar and 1/4 of a Knorr chicken bouillon cube (do not add additional salt and pepper).
Mix together with above ingredients.
Serves 8.

title: braised venison tips
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of the margarine. Add mushrooms and cook
until
they
just begin to turn brown. Put in a
large,
deep casserole.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons of margarine and oil
to same skillet and heat.
Brown meat on all sides; remove
to
the casserole with mushrooms.
Pour the 3/4 cup bouillon,
soy
sauce,
garlic
and
onion in skillet. Over low heat,
stir, scraping bottom to remove all particles. Blend
the cornstarch
with
the
cup
bouillon.
Add
to skillet; stirring
constantly,
cook
until mixture has thickened.
Pour over
meat
and mushrooms in casserole.
Cover and cook at 275° for
hours.
Stir
in
the mushroom soup. When smooth, check
seasoning, then serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: christopher's popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place a cast-iron popover pan or 8 custard cups on a baking sheet and set in oven to preheat.
In medium bowl, beat the eggs until frothy.
Beat in the milk and butter.
Fold in the flour, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Carefully remove the hot popover pan from the oven and grease with vegetable shortening.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the persimmon and soda; let stand while creaming together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla, lemon juice and brandy, then add persimmon and mix until blended.

title: giant pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place butter in an 11 3/4-inch cast-iron skillet and put in oven to melt and heat while mixing batter.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart baking dish, stir together beans, onion, ketchup and bacon.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: seasoned bread crumbs
directions: Put scraps of bread or rolls in a dry, warm place for 2 days. Put bread in a blender and crumb.
To each cup of crumbs, add remaining ingredients.
These are good for breading chicken, pork chops, veal or fish.

title: marinated salmon salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and pour over cooked salmon. Marinate at least 2 hours or longer, turning occasionally.
Serve cold on lettuce.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: Fry bacon well and drain. Melt cheese and soup slowly, add onions and bacon, keep warm. A crockpot works well. Serve with cubed French or sourdough bread.

title: south carolina chicken bog
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from bones and place back into chicken broth.
Add rice and cook until rice is tender.
Add sausages (sliced into 1-inch pieces), eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until sausages are hot.
Enjoy!

title: buttermilk loaf cake
directions: May the road rise to meet you.
May the wind be always at your back.
May the sun shine warm upon your face, the rain fall soft upon your fields, and until we meet again, may God hold you in the palm of His hand.

title: wiener sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix all ingredients.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon boil
directions: Cut
salmon
up
into
2-inch squares.	Bring to a boil 6-quarts water
with
1/2 cup salt in 14-inch Dutch oven.
Add potatoes, onions and spices.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add salmon and boil 12 minutes longer.
Drain off liquid and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop and grate everything as small as possible.
Mix together well.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add syrup and melted candy bar.
Add salt and flour.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Alternate flour and milk, stirring well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: easy shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor.
Process until mixed well.
Chill for several hours.
When ready to serve, hollow out the center of the loaf of bread and cut the removed portion into cubes.
Place the shrimp mixture in the bread, using the cubed pieces to dip with.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Butter baking sheet.
Mix brown sugar, corn syrup, granulated sugar and water in 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in peanuts and peanut butter. Microwave on High for another 3 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Add butter and vanilla, then microwave until candy thermometer reads 300°, about 4 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour onto baking sheet and smooth with metal spatula.
Let cool.
Store in airtight tin.
Makes 1 pound.

title: blueberry batter cake
directions: Place berries in an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and spread over berries.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch and sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar and beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.
Enjoy.

title: stack-a-roll stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Sprinkle onions over beef (reserve 1/2 cup).
Sprinkle sliced mushrooms over onions.
Combine 1/2 cup sour cream and mushroom soup in saucepan.
Heat until boiling point is reached.
Pour over ground beef mixture.
Cut biscuits in 1/2 (1/2 moon shape) and arrange around casserole. Sprinkle 1/2 cup onions in center.
Beat egg, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup sour cream and pour over biscuits around edge of casserole. Bake at 350° until biscuits are browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: viola's watergate pie
directions: Mix in square 8 x 8-inch pan the flour, pecans, sugar and butter, then pat down good, making crust.
Bake until brown (light) at 350°.
Next, mix cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Then spread some Cool Whip on top of cheese.
In medium bowl, mix milk and the two boxes of pudding until thick; pour over Cool Whip.
Spread a thin layer of Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle with a few chopped pecans.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, mix 1/4 cup soup, hamburger, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape into big firm patties.
In skillet, cook patties until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Pour soup and mushrooms over patties and put lid on skillet and reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until done.
You can do this with round steak, too.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits; add butter and grated cheese.
Beat eggs and add milk; add egg mixture to grits.
Put in a well-greased long baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix by hand the pudding and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix and put into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with 6 ounces of chocolate chips and 1 cup of nuts.
(If desired, these can be mixed into the batter.)
Bake for 55 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: fish espanola
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish and arrange fish fillets. Saute celery, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender.
Add flour and blend.
Add tomatoes, breaking up as you stir.
Add remainder except for sherry; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and add sherry.
Pour mixture over fish and bake uncovered at 425° for about 12 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: flank steak favorite
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Score flank steak on both sides and marinate 4 hours or overnight (overnight is best!).
Grill outdoors or under broiler on each side to desired amount.
Slice in thin diagonal strips for serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa; add egg yolks and milk.
Cook in iron skillet.
After it thickens, add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shells.
Use whites for meringue.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chow chow
directions: Grate cabbage and tomatoes; combine with salt.
Let set for 1 hour, then drain.
Combine all ingredients; let boil 15 to 20 minutes, until tender, then pack in hot jars and seal.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in buttered dish.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Place cut-up chicken and onion in the water and cook slowly until tender; add salt.
Remove and cut the meat into 1-inch pieces and return to broth together with corn that has been cut from the cob, celery and seasoning.
Continue to simmer.
For a richer broth, add 4 bouillon (chicken) cubes to the pot.
Add 2 cups of cooked noodles or 1 recipe of rivels (recipe follows).

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar with mashed peaches.
Add peaches to other ingredients.
Mix and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: maryann's fish casserole supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dot bottom of 8-inch square baking dish with butter or margarine.
Crumble crackers to cover bottom of dish.
Saute chopped spinach in oil with hot pepper and chopped garlic if desired.
Spread over crackers.
Add mushrooms, then fish fillets, cut in small pieces.
Pour heavy cream over all and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and more cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop artichoke hearts and garlic. Combine all ingredients.
Turn into a casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square cake pan.
Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler over hot, but not boiling water.
When chocolate is melted, turn off stove.
Lift off top of double boiler.
Set aside to cool.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into large bowl.
Set aside.
Break eggs into another bowl
and beat until frothy.
Beat sugar into eggs, a little at a time.
Add chocolate mixture and vanilla to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Stir flour mixture into egg mixture.
Add nuts and coconut.
Stir well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Spread evenly with the back of spoon.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Set on cake rack.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift twice with salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and blend in sugar; add egg and beat until fluffy.
Add bran and milk; stir until well mixed, then let stand a few minutes until bran takes up most of the liquid.
Finally add flour mixture, stirring only until flour has disappeared.
Fill buttered muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until muffins are nicely browned.
Serve piping hot with plenty of butter.
Makes 8 large or 12 small muffins.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Blend until thoroughly combined.
Drain water from shrimp and break shrimp into pieces. Chill mixture 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: cider syrup
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg in a saucepan. Stir in cider and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Blend in butter.
Serve over pancakes.
Top with dot of sour cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, eggs and A.1. steak sauce and Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing together.
Shape in loaf pan.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit whip
directions: Soften the gelatin in the lime juice.
Combine lime rind, syrup, sugar, salt and gelatin in a saucepan and heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Blend in several drops of almond extract.
Then chill until slightly thickened.
Whip evaporated milk in a chilled bowl until light and fluffy and fold in gelatin mixture.
Fold in fruit cocktail and chill until partially set. Line serving dish with ladyfingers and spoon fruit mixture into dish.
Chill several hours and garnish with other fruits.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Place lettuce or spinach in the bottom of a bowl.
Layer mushrooms and broccoli or peas over lettuce or spinach.
Then layer carrots.
Arrange egg slices and bacon over vegetables.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded cheese and green onion.
Top with salad dressing of choice and sprinkle with remaining cheese and a little onion. Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours.
Before serving, toss.

title: stir-fry snow peas and pork
directions: In a wok set to highest temperature, pour oil.
Add pork and stir-fry 2 minutes or until pork is no longer pink.
Add celery, onion, mushrooms, water chestnuts, snow peas, red peppers and ginger root.
Cook over heat for 3 minutes.
Remove to a warm bowl.

title: slushy punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 9 cups hot water.
Dissolve sugar in 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Mix jello and sugar mixtures.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 hours before serving.
Shortly before serving, chop and let stand, then add two 28 ounce bottles ginger ale.
One gallon milk carton holds 1/2 recipe for freezing.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and mix in rest of ingredients in pan.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed in 9 x 14-inch pan or 10 x 14-inch pan; cool.
Prepare pudding as directed and refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes.
Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly add instant pudding and keep whipping to keep smooth.
Add whipped topping until blended.
Place pineapple over cool cake and top with cream cheese and pudding mixture.
Top with coconut and chopped nuts.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine beans (drained), soup and milk in casserole.
Cover with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease bottom of a 12-inch iron skillet. In a medium bowl, mix eggs, butter and milk. Add dry ingredients. Add corn and jalapeno last. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: richard's ham
directions: Put all ingredients, except cheese, in roasting pan.
Sprinkle top with cloves.
Bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: kathy's strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's gelatin fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of boiling water and lemon gelatin.
Add 1 cup ice cubes; stir until melted, then add drained pineapple.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking pan; refrigerate until set.
Repeat with orange gelatin, remaining water and ice cubes; stir in marshmallows.
Pour over lemon layer, then refrigerate until set.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, grated onion, eggs, milk, half of brown sugar, half of catsup, salt and pepper to taste.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Can bake in oven for 15 minutes on cookie sheet, drain fat off.
Mix in boiler or slow cooker butter, garlic powder, rest of brown sugar and catsup, and vinegar.
Start cooking on medium heat.
Put meat balls in and simmer until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, water and rice. Pour in baking dish or roaster. Place cut up chicken on top. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is done. May use sliced potatoes instead of rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown chopped meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Cut peppers; fill.
Put tomato sauce over peppers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add milk and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Slowly boil 12 to 15 minutes, stirring while boiling.
Remove from heat and add coconut and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix together
and let set for a few minutes.
Tint with food coloring.

title: quick english toffee
directions: Sprinkle pecans at the bottom of a buttered 9-inch pie plate. Melt 1/2 cup butter in saucepan, add sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 290° (hard crack stage).
Pour toffee over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over the top.
When chocolate is melted, spread with a spatula.
Cool. Refrigerate and break into pieces.

title: quick black bean soup
directions: Heat oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic; saute until onion is tender, about 10 minutes.
Mix in tomatoes with their juices, chilies and thyme. Reduce heat to low and simmer until vegetables are very soft, about 10 minutes.
Add beans and 2 cups chicken broth.
Puree soup in batches in processor or blender until smooth. Return soup to pot.
(Can be prepared 4 days ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.) Bring soup to simmer. Thin with more broth if necessary. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Garnish with sour cream and sliced green onions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar and stick oleo.
Add eggs and vanilla, beat until light and fluffy.
Spread this mixture over crumbs in pan.
Slice bananas lengthwise in thin slices and place over pudding layer.
Add drained crushed pineapple and spread evenly over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with grated nuts and dot with cherries (if desired).

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Scrape and clean carrots.
Slice in half.
Add water and salt. Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Uncover and cook 4 minutes or until liquid evaporates.
Add orange slices, syrup and butter.
Cook on low heat.
Turn carrots to coat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: fruit pies
directions: Line muffin pans with rich pie dough and fill with batter and bake.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine 1 cup cereal, boiling water and oil; set aside. Combine flour, salt, sugar, soda and remaining cereal.
Add eggs and buttermilk to flour mixture.
Stir in oil mixture.
Add raisins, spoon batter into well-greased muffins pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat chopped onion and 1/2 cup water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until onion is tender. Add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Partially cover saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Makes 10 servings.
Per serving: 205 calories and 2 gm fat.

title: chopped bread(mexican)
directions: Take dough and flatten out.
Add ingredients to dough.
Take four corners and pinch together in the middle.
Chop dough and ingredients into pieces and combine well.
Shape into a ball. Place on lined baking sheet.
Let dough sit at room temperature until it doubles in volume.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into pieces and serve hot.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, sliced eggs, soup, cheese and peas.
Melt oleo and crumble crackers; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with crackers.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly, butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Blend in flour and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack into sterilized jars.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil and pour over okra in jars.
Put into hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Ready to eat in 3 to 4 weeks.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Serve chilled.
Yields 15 servings.

title: crustless fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan over low heat or in double boiler.
Add sugar and blend well.
Add eggs; beat well with wooden spoon.
Add flour and vanilla and blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate and top with nuts.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Good to have one in your freezer for unexpected company.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil and saute
garlic lightly.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer until quite thick.
In a large bowl, combine meat, beaten eggs, cheese and broken up bread that has been moistened in water.
Mix and form into small balls and brown lightly in a skillet.
Add to the sauce and simmer until meatballs are done.

title: dried beef macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a covered dish.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake covered for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove lid and bake for 10 more minutes uncovered. Serves approximately 4.

title: zucchini crusted pizza
directions: *Ex. tomatoes, bell peppers, olives garlic, sauteed mushrooms, extra cheeses etc.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add vanilla and butter.
Add flour and milk. Beat well.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold them into the batter. Cook in waffle iron.
You can also make pancakes on a griddle.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix buttermilk with soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown (12 minutes).

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; place in 8 to 9-inch square baking dish.
Add tomato sauce.
Top with cheese slices.
Prepare biscuit mix with milk and roll into thin biscuits.
Place biscuits on top of cheese slices.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes or until biscuits are done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stroganoff, italian style
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Drain and add sour cream and dry stroganoff mix.
While this is simmering, slice French bread lengthwise and butter it.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place hamburger mixture on buttered bread.
Top with cheese and bake in 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add 2 cups flour; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar; place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Flatten with fork.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool.
Store, tightly covered, at room temperature.

title: crock-pot beef vegetable soup
directions: Add all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on high for 4 to 4 1/2 hours or on low for 8 to 9 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Soup can also be frozen for later use.

title: mrs. margaret walker's chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use the broth that the hen was cooked in as liquid.
If broth does not cover mixture, you can add enough water to cover.
Cook in 350° oven for 3 hours, stirring frequently.
When liquid cooks down, add water to keep moist.
I put grated cheese on top.

title: best deal cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: chops madrid
directions: Saute chops in oleo until browned.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir sauce and water and pour over chops.
Let simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onions, "undrained" mushrooms, olives and wine and let cook 15 minutes or longer.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Pour into buttered tube pan that has been covered with pecan pieces.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Form into 1-inch balls, pressing firmly. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden brown around edges. Cool 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet. Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream apple spice cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 10-inch tube or streusel cake pan.
In large bowl, blend cake mix and remaining cake ingredients except raisins at low speed until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed; stir in raisins.
Pour 2/3 of batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle 2/3 cup streusel mix evenly over batter in pan.
Spread with remaining batter; top with remaining streusel mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pan on wire rack 30 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack, streusel side up completely before glazing.
Blend glaze mix with 2 teaspoons water until smooth and drizzle over cake.

title: key lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add lime rind and juice. Pour slowly into beaten egg yolk, stirring constantly.
Add condensed milk and bitters.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks will form.
Fold into gelatin mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Garnish with lime slices or whipped topping, if desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter. Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top and pour remaining 1/4 cup butter over cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pats banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Add beaten egg, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very moist and delicious.

title: patti's chicken wings
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook for 6 minutes at medium heat until thick.
Marinate in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Baste occasionally.
Sauce can also be used for other chicken.
Makes ample sauce.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Slowly stir half the mixture into well beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg mixture into remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue, if desired.

title: grandma's tator soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion, butter and salt in water for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add milk and pepper (to taste).
In a bowl, mix together flour, 1 cup milk and salt to form thickening.
Pour into potato soup.
Stir thoroughly until boiling.
Simmer for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: pineapple cream dessert
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows in a saucepan and heat until marshmallows have been dissolved.
Cool.
To the whipped cream add pineapple and cooled mixture and pour into a pan lined with rolled graham crackers.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs and allow to set in refrigerator about 4 hours.

title: back yard shrimp
directions: You will need one pack of wooden skewers.

title: green salad
directions: Mix together with just enough mayonnaise to coat vegetables. Keep refrigerated.

title: durgin pork baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Parboil in the morning with 1/2 teaspoon baking soda 5 minutes.
Run a cup of water through beans in strainer.
Dice bacon or salt pork.
Cut in half.
Place 1/2 in bottom of beanpot with onion.
Add beans and place 1/2 bacon/salt pork on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over beans just until liquid shows.
Do not stir.
Cook at 300° for 6 hours, adding liquid ingredients as needed.

title: not your mama's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Cut in Crisco.
Put potatoes through food processor. Measure 2 cups and add to dry ingredients.
Mix with hands to a soft ball.
May need to add a little more flour.
Pat out on floured board.

Cut out with 1 1/2-inch cutter and place on greased baking sheet. Brush tops liberally with melted butter. Cook 18 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with butter or with country ham. Great made with small cutter and used as an appetizer.

title: lima-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables separately as directed	and
drain.
Mix together in casserole.
Mix together
remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Mix 1 cup Rice Krispies
with
1/4 pound butter
and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for
20	minutes
or until bubbly.

title: custard noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces and stir into noodles.
Add sugar to eggs and beat.
Add milk and mix well. Add melted margarine and vanilla.
Add to drained noodles and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can top with cinnamon, sugar and chopped nuts (optional).

title: leftover turkey chowder with sage
directions: Heat a 4 to 6-quart heavy pot over low heat and add the bacon. Once it has rendered a few tablespoons of fat, increase the heat to medium and cook until the bacon is crisp and golden brown.

Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of the fat, leaving the bacon in the pot. Add the butter, onion, celery, thyme and sage and saute, stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon for 10 to 12 minutes, until the vegetables are softened but not brown.
Add the potatoes and the turkey stock.
The stock should barely cover the potatoes.
If it doesn't, add more stock or water to cover.
Turn up the heat and bring to a boil.
Cover and cook the potatoes vigorously for about 10 minutes, until they are soft on the outside but still firm in the center.
If the broth has not thickened, lightly smash a few potatoes against the side of the pot and cook a minute or two longer to release the starch.
Add the turkey and simmer for 5 more minutes.
If you have added more than 1 pound of turkey meat, add more stock (up to 1 cup for 1 1/2 pounds of meat).
Remove the chowder from the heat, stir in the cream and season to taste with salt and black pepper.
If you are not serving the chowder within the hour, let it cook a bit, then refrigerate; cover.

title: basted chicken
directions: Put chicken in a pan and bake at 350°.
While baking, baste with the Russian dressing.
Approximately 10 minutes before the chicken is done, pour the entire can of fruit cocktail over the chicken.
Cook at least until the fruit cocktail is warmed through.

title: mock salmon dip
directions: Warm soup add cream cheese until melted and smooth.
Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 c. hot water.
In large bowl add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.
Remove from mold onto serving plate.
Serve with HiHo's or any cracker.

title: alligator sauce picante(a great cook ahead appetizer or party food)
directions: May wish to add peppers in 1/2 teaspoon amounts and taste, adjust to your own tongue tolerance.

title: meatball vegetable stew
directions: Combine beef and bread crumbs.
Shape into 12 balls and roll in flour.
Brown meatballs in hot oil with onion.
Add carrots, broth, pepper and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve hot, sprinkled with parsley.
Delicious, fast and easy.
Goes well with cornbread.

title: "refrigerator pickles"
directions: Wash cucumbers; soak in ice cold water (salt water) with onions.
Bring the sugar, vinegar, celery and mustard seed to a boil to make a syrup.
Let the cucumbers soak until the syrup is cooled.
Drain off salt water.
Pour syrup over cucumbers and pack in jars.
Refrigerate.
Leave some room at the top of the jar.

title: florey's crab imperial
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic powder (this is the topping).
Blend mayonnaise, cream cheese, mustard and cayenne pepper.
Fold crabmeat into mixture.
Spread mixture with crab shells (if using shells, coat with butter) or a 7 x 11-inch shallow pan or casserole dish.
Top with crumb mixture then the Cheddar cheese.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes at 375°, or until slightly brown and bubbly.
Garnish with lemons and serve immediately.
A good Chardonnay would make a nice accompaniment.

title: mrs. h's famous fudge
directions: Blend milk, sugar and butter.
Put on stove and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil 8 minutes, still stirring constantly.
Don't have mixture too hot or mixture will burn.
Mix cream and chocolate chips in large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over cream; add chips and stir only until chips are melted and blended thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts and blend well.
Pour immediately on buttered cookie sheet or pan with 1-inch sides.
Take 3 hours to set before cutting.

title: vanderbilt fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with apricot juice only until smooth.
Do not beat.
Add fruit and nuts; mix.
Add a little of pineapple juice, if needed.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix well with a pastry blender until fine grains.
Line two 8-inch pans with brown paper.
Put 1/2 of the mixture in each pan, then press with your hand into the pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
When cakes are light brown, they are done.

title: kellen's favorite banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, sour cream and bananas.
Mix thoroughly and stir in nuts.
Pour into 3 regular sized loaf pans or 5 small loaf pans.
Let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage-stuffed duckling
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Transfer to bowl; stir in bread, parsley, apple, celery, onion, thyme and butter.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Toss with 2 teaspoons water.
Rub cavity of duckling with salt; stuff with sausage mix.
Tie legs to tail.
Twist wing tips under back.
Place bird, breast up, on rack in a roasting pan.
Prick skin all over with a fork.
Roast, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender. Spoon off fat as necessary.
Place any reserved stuffing in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water.
Cover. Bake casserole during last 30 minutes.
Serve with duckling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and oregano, then spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together and set aside the flour, sugar, cocoa and soda. Boil together the margarine, oil and water.
Add boiled mixture to flour mixture immediately and mix well, then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into prepared sheet pan (I use Pam).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with favorite icing.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim the meat of all possible fat; meat should be semi-froze for easier slicing.
Slice meat into 1/2-inch strips; marinate overnight in a shallow glass dish in the refrigerator.
Turn occasionally to coat each piece thoroughly.
Drain well on paper towel, patting each piece dry.
Lay strips in a single layer on an oven rack; do not overlap.
Place a cookie sheet or foil underneath to catch drippings.
Roast at lowest possible temperature (125° to 140°) for 8 to 12 hours, leaving oven door ajar.

title: quick sticky peach pinwheels
directions: In a small saucepan, heat and stir preserves until melted. Pour into a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Spread evenly. Separate, but do not uncoil, the refrigerated breadsticks. Arrange coiled dough atop the preserves in the baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden.
Immediately invert onto a platter.
Sprinkle with the chocolate pieces.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in 1/2 of the butter with oregano and salt until tender, about 5 minutes.

title: cajun fish with rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet in the oil, cook the oregano and pepper until done.
Add remaining ingredients, except fish.
Heat to boiling.
Arrange fish in soup mixture.
Reduce heat. Cover.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until fish is done.
Serve with the rice. Serves 4.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook meat, drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and stir good.
In casserole dish, spread beans, cover with beef mixture.
Pour soup over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and then olives.
Cook in oven until bubbly.
Pour sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with green onions.
Arrange tortilla chips around edge of dish.

title: quick rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup water and stir until dissolved; add remaining water.
Mix all ingredients together, adding the flour last.
Spoon into greased muffin tins (fill 1/2 full).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pineapple puffs
directions: Cut marshmallows in half.
Add to drained can of pineapple. Whip cream and add to mixture.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour.
Crush graham crackers fine and drop tablespoon of cream mixture into crackers.
Coat heavily.
Roll around with fingers until heavily coated.
Lay on waxed paper.
Put cherry in on top of puff.

title: barbecue pizza
directions: Put on crust and cook.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate biscuits into 20 pieces. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits into melted margarine, then roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits in single layer, overlapping slightly in round baking dish.
Place an apple slice between each biscuit and around outer edge of baking dish.
Mix nuts and raisins with remaining cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mary l's chicken with almonds
directions: Bring pan of salted water to boil and cook chicken 2 minutes and drain.
Remove skin and bone.
Dry on paper towels.
Mix flour with salt and pepper and dust breasts in it.
Heat half butter in pan.
Put in chicken and brown slowly each side.
Add the lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.
Cover the pan and saute gently over low heat until chicken is tender.
Remove the chicken, set aside and add almonds to the pan with garlic, onion and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Shake pan and brown almonds.
Stir in remaining butter with wine.
Return chicken to pan and reheat. Arrange chicken in warm serving dish.
Spoon almond and sauce over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix ingredients in the order that they are listed. Pour into pie crust. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: scallops oriental
directions: Preheat broiler 5 minutes.
Rinse fresh scallops in cold water or thaw frozen scallops.
Place in baking dish.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl; mix well.
Roll into meatballs.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 minutes; turn and bake for another 15 minutes.
Add to sauce.

title: yummy dessert
directions: Mix together and put in bottom of 2-quart glass baking dish.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop on pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in cheesecake pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: becky's mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and put in refrigerator to cool while melting cheese.
In double boiler, melt Velveeta with small amount of milk. Add Ro-Tel.
In baking dish, grease and put chips in heavy layer. Then layer chicken.
In large bowl, add cheese sauce, cream of chicken soup, onion and 1/2 cup milk.
Mix all until smooth.
Pour all over chips and chicken.
Put shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack over all.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix together.
Makes enough for a 20 pound turkey.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and beat well. Stir
in
applesauce.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt.
Stir and beat until well blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put batter into greased and lightly floured Bundt pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Turn cake out of pan and glaze with apple
glaze (one cup powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons apple juice and food coloring).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Hint:
For best results, add bananas just before serving, as they do brown.

title: rib-eye roast with gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine garlic, salt, peppercorns and thyme in a small bowl.
Press evenly onto surface of meat.
Place roast in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of meat.
Roast for 18 minutes per pound for rare, 22 minutes per pound for medium or to desired doneness.
Let roast stand for 15 minutes before carving.

title: cranberry crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie crust 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon.
Pour into prepared pie crust. In small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Spoon evenly over cheese mixture. In medium mixing bowl, cut butter into flour and remaining 2 tablespoons sugar until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over cranberry mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbly and golden.
Cool.
Serve at room temperature or chill thoroughly. Great at Christmas!

title: chicken croissants
directions: Boil chicken until easy to peel off skin and tear apart. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pull chicken off bones; place chicken on the wide end of the croissants and roll up to the small end.
Bend ends and place in casserole dish.
Mix milk, cheese and soup; pour over the croissants.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: paprika chicken baked with mushroom soup
directions: Mix together flour, paprika and pepper.
Roll chicken parts in mixture until well coated.
Melt margarine in a roasting pan or casserole, 9 x 13-inches.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down in pan (may be skinned).
Spoon melted margarine over pieces.
Pour soup over top of chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all of the ingredients and chill.

title: avocado-stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes thoroughly. Pat dry. Rub potatoes lightly with oil.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are soft to the touch.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and flour together in pan.
Boil vinegar and water.
Pour boiling mixture slowly into first mixture, stirring continually.
When mixed, bring all to boil until thickened.
Yields one pint.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water:
butterscotch morsels and peanut butter.
Remove from heat; mix in chow mein noodles and miniature marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix ingredients together well and store in an air tight container.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package, adding pie filling.
Bake in one or two large greased oblong pans (thin layers).
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt wax, sugar and syrup.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts pop.
Add soda and salt.
Stir well.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: quick cobbler pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour into melted buttered pan.
Pour sweetened fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Beat
together
eggs,
sugar, salt and vanilla in small bowl at medium speed until light, about 1 minute.
Add melted butter and
continue
beating until well mixed.
On low speed mix
in flour and cocoa.
Stir in coconut or chocolate chips, if
desired. Spread
evenly
in
8-inch square greased baking dish appropriate for use in microwave oven.
Cook on High 6 to 10
minutes, giving dish a quarter turn every 2 minutes.
When done,
top
will spring
back when lightly touched.
Cut when cold.

title: '59 ford bran muffins
directions: Soak wheat bran in 2 cups boiling water while preparing the rest.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add all-bran cereal; mix well.
Add soaked wheat bran.
Fill greased muffin tins and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 400°.
Pour remaining in glass jars and refrigerate.
Will keep a month.
Do not stir.
Spoon from jar into muffin tin.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening for 2 minutes at medium speed. Gradually add sugar, beat for 5-7 minutes.
Add eggs 1 at a time just till yellow disappears. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add together alternating with milk; beginning and ending with flour. Mix just till blended.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Bake 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10-15 minutes.

title: frances' caramel candy
directions: Put 2 cups of sugar in a heavy iron skillet.
In a pot, put the other 2 cups of sugar, whipping cream, milk and salt.
Put both skillet and pot over heat.
Stir skillet with silver spoon and pot with wooden spoon.

title: blackberry jello salad
directions: Melt blackberry Jell-O in boiling water.
Cut up cream cheese in this and soften with a spoon.
Add remaining ingredients. Allow to congeal in a large bowl or mold.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Heat 1/2 cup of the chocolate chips and the margarine in heavy-duty 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted.
Mix baking mix, sugar, vanilla, eggs and chocolate mixture; spread in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate chips.

title: shaker pickles
directions: Slice the pickles and onions.
Mix the sugar and vinegar, also the salt, alum, celery seed and turmeric.
Do not heat vinegar and spices.
Pour mixture over the onions and pickles.
Place in jar in refrigerator. Shake once a day for 6 days while kept in the refrigerator for 3 months. Add 1 tablespoon of mixed pickling spice for taste.

title: hot bread(pop overs)
directions: Combine milk, flour, oil and salt. Beat on high speed for 1 minute. Add eggs one at a time. Grease 8 muffin tins. Fill cups 2/3 full. Set in cold oven. Turn heat to 425° and bake 35 minutes. Let stand a minute.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Parboil eggplant until tender and mash through colander. Beat.
Add other ingredients and bake after sprinkling top generously with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: loring's favorite molasses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in egg until well combined.
Beat in molasses.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat in dry ingredients by thirds, alternating with 1/2 cup hot water.
Mix in raisins and nuts (if using).
Drop by tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a loaf as you would meat loaf. Make sauce.

title: muffins
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth in blender or processor.
Serve with vegetables.

title: sweet and sour dill pickles
directions: Put dill in bottom of jar first.
Then slice cucumbers thin and add to jar along with celery and onion.
Bring to a boil the last four ingredients.
Pour over pickles and seal.

title: reese's peanut butter bars(no bake)
directions: Combine with fork or pastry blender.
Stir in 1 2/3 cups crushed graham crackers.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt 2 cups chocolate chips and spread over bars.
Cut before chocolate sets.
Rich and delicious!

title: wilma's mexican hominy
directions: Brown sausage, breaking into small pieces as you fry it.
Put it out on paper towels to drain off excess grease.
In a large bowl, mix sausage and all other ingredients well, except chips and half the grated cheese.
Spray baking dish with Pam and sprinkle a few crushed chips on bottom of dish.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.
Heat in a hot 400 degree oven 15-18 minutes until bubbly and hot.
Sprinkle rest of chips, then remaining cheese on top. Heat 5 to 7 minutes longer until cheese begins to melt.
Serve hot.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Peel hard-boiled eggs.
Crumble sausage in bowl and add oregano, cheese and herbs.
Mix together.
Pack sausage mix around eggs.
Dip in beaten egg; roll in bread crumbs.
Fry all sides in 1/2 inch of oil.
Drain on paper towels.
May be eaten hot or cold.
One egg is filling.
Great for supper with some fresh fruit.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, flour, white sugar and egg; place in a baking dish.
Cover with mixture of brown sugar, remaining flour and butter; press over rhubarb.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Heat brown sugar and water on stove top. Bring to a boil. Place apples in a shallow baking dish. Pour syrup over apples. Bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: leave it to beaver chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients; flour, salt, baking soda.
Add chocolate chips and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flavoring, cream and flour mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle small amount of cinnamon and sugar on top.

title: apple pudding torte
directions: Mix and let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over pieces of torte when served.
Heat leftover sauce when serving again.

title: christmas pound cake
directions: Cream butter with cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients 3 times and add alternately with the milk. Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in one bowl.
Spray cooking dish with Pam.
Pour in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until top is lightly brown.
Can be done ahead of time.
Reheats very well in microwave when baked in glass pie dish.
Cut in wedges.
Serve with salad for light lunch.
If baked in square pan, cut in squares for appetizers.

title: beef or pork soy sauce marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to 2 to 4 pounds lean beef steak or pork chops.
Refrigerate and marinate 1 to 2 days.
Barbecue, broil or panfry.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Wash, peel and slice carrots.
Wash and quarter red potatoes.
Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap roast, carrots and potatoes in foil and cook until tender.

title: ham and vegetables
directions: Place ham bone in kettle or dutch oven.
Arrange cabbage around the ham bone.
Add carrots, potatoes, and onions.
Add enough water to cover vegetables, and slowly simmer until vegetables are done.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking powder in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Then measure in milk, oil, vanilla and nuts (optional).
Stir until smooth.
On top of mixture, sprinkle brown sugar, then sprinkle cocoa.
Then pour hot tap water on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet over medium heat. Drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients; pour mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: ratatouille
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Saute onions and garlic.
Brown eggplant first, then zucchini and yellow squash.
Add tomatoes last, then sprinkle sugar over mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk. Knead slightly.
Roll to 5/8-inch thickness. Bake at 425° for 10 or more minutes or until slightly brown.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Use as much or as little as you think you would like.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream both sugars, margarine, shortening and eggs.
Add baking soda and baking powder.
Stir until blended completely.
Add oatmeal, flour and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel chocolate bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler. Cover and place over boiling water until melted, stirring occasionally. Keep warm.

title: crab puffs supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine crab meat, cheese, onions, Worcestershire and mustard in medium size bowl; mix well.
Set aside.

title: annie's favorite mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press equal portions onto bottom of 24 paper-lined muffin cups. In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 2 tablespoons) into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Chill.
Garnish with cherry pie filling or own choice.

title: easy chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In an 11 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, put the chicken on the bottom.
Pour cream of chicken soup over all.
Mix stuffing mix in a bowl with egg beaten with 1 cup broth.
Spread over soup.
Pour 2 cups broth over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
If stuffing becomes dry while cooking, pour another cup of broth over it.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in 3 well-greased layer cake pans for 30 to 35 minutes or 1 tube pan for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: best ever sunday fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in plastic bag; shake to mix.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, milk and lemon juice; stir well.
Skin chicken.
Place 2 or 3 pieces in bag and shake well.
Dip in egg mixture, then return to bag and shake again.
Repeat with remaining chicken.

title: almond velvet fudge cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Measure remaining ingredients into bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
