Do not underbake.

title: bachelor button cookies
directions: Blend together brown sugar and shortening.
Mix additional ingredients with brown sugar and shortening.
Roll into round balls, flatten with a fork.
Add raisins, nuts and chocolate chips or leave plain.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes on medium until tender with margarine, onion, celery, carrots, celery flakes, salt and pepper.
Add milk and simmer.
To thicken, mix cornstarch in small amount of water until blended, then add to soup (flour can be used, if preferred).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, cocoa and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla until all are mixed well.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: far east eggplant
directions: Cook all ingredients, except cheese and bacon, in skillet until tender.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Brown under broiler. Serves 4.

title: macaroni dish #4
directions: Cook
macaroni	and
put in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients
together
and	cover macaroni.
Crush cheese Ritz crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: iced lemon
directions: Mix together hot water, sweetener and lemon juice.
Heat. Dissolve gelatin in hot water mixture.
Chill until set.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Fold in whipped gelatin mixture. Serve in 4 sherbet glasses.
Yield:
2 servings.
Carbohydrate 1.3 g, protein .4 g, fat 0 g, calories 20.
One serving = free food exchange.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour and Parmesan cheese in plastic bag.
Shake a few potato cubes in bag at a time and put in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
With spatula, turn over and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies(no eggs, no sugar)
directions: Mix together.
Form into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix flour, sugar, sour cream. and beer.
Pour into a 9 x 11 inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes and brush with butter.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Blend ingredients and cook until thickened.
Pour into 8-inch baked pie crust.

title: cherry bisque
directions: Thoroughly chill milk overnight.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice, rind, salt and sugar.
Stir well.
Jell slightly.

title: currant biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, Crisco, baking powder and currants.
Mix like pie dough.
Beat egg in a cup and fill with milk to measure 1 cup.
Add to dough; mix and
knead.
Flatten to about 1/2-inch and cut with a doughnut cutter or glass.
Place on prepared cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Check after 12 minutes.
I like them softer rather than too baked as they tend to firm up after taking out of the oven.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except candy Kisses.
Roll into small balls and then in white sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
As soon as they come from oven, press a candy Kiss into the center of each cookie. Remove to rack to cool.
Store in a single layer; do not stack.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream well the margarine or butter and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, baking soda and vanilla extract.
Chill overnight.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake or they will be hard.

title: curried crabmeat spread
directions: Pick over crabmeat, discarding any cartilage.
Shred the meat, then blend with all ingredients.
Taste for seasoning; serve with toast triangles, crisp crackers or Melba rounds.
Yield:
10 servings; double recipe for a cocktail party for 20.

title: grilled smokey pork ribs
directions: Place ribs in large saucepan. Add enough water to cover ribs. Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender. Melt butter in small saucepan. Fry garlic until lightly browned. Stir in 1/4 cup water, Worcestershire, liquid smoke, brown sugar, ketchup, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place ribs on grill. Cover and cook 20 minutes, turning and brushing with sauce every 5 minutes. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal and flour.
Add corn and egg.
Stir in onion, salt and soda.
Drop by teaspoon into deep fryer.
Fry until puppies rise to top of pot and golden brown.
If batter is too thin, add a bit more meal.

title: dot's pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter or margarine and shortening together well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in tube or long loaf pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato pie 1
directions: Mash potatoes.
Beat eggs.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add potatoes and milk.
Bake crust at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour potato mixture into crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Defrost and prepare spinach.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reserve a few crushed saltines.
Pour mixture into baking dish or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip and refrigerate.
Cream the cream cheese, mayo and sugar.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts; fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Freeze.
Serves 18 to 24.

title: company breakfast sausage
directions: Break the bread into small pieces.
Spread on bottom of greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Brown sausage in skillet. Pour off grease. Spread over bread.
Spread grated Cheddar on top of sausage.
Beat eggs with milk. Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Pour over all.
Can be prepared the night before and refrigerated.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with black bread and butter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
In a 9 x 11-inch pan, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: egg nog
directions: Whip together Eagle Brand milk and Egg Beaters.
Whip together milk and vanilla. Mix together. Put in punch bowl with Cool Whip.

title: rum cake
directions: Spray Bundt cake pan.
Crumble pecans onto bottom of pan, followed by maraschino cherry halves.
Mix rest of ingredients with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into Bundt cake pan with the pecans and cherries in the bottom.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and while still hot, pour Rum Glaze over cake.
Leave in pan 30 minutes.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Simmer all ingredients together in a large saucepan for 10 minutes.
Strain.
Serve in tea cups or mugs.

title: chocolate dump bar
directions: Mix and "dump" all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Mix until moistened.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: berry jam
directions: You will also need 2 dozen pint canning jars.

title: fruit cake cookies *
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add alternating with wine.
Stir in fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven (275° to 300°) until golden brown.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix together oats, flour and brown sugar. Cut in butter until crumbly. Press half mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Break the cranberry sauce up with a fork and spread on top of crumb mixture. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 45 minutes. Cool. Cut into squares or bars. Makes 9 servings.

title: lemon cole salad
directions: Shred a large head of cabbage very fine.
Combine sugar and lemon juice.
The sugar will appear dampened.
Combine with cabbage.
Place in refrigerator for at least 1/2 day.
Stir several times.

title: turkey - black bean chili
directions: Coat dutch oven with cooking spray and place over medium high heat until hot.
Add onion and celery with cooking spray and suate till tender.
Transfer to a blender.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Add 1/2 of the beans and all of the liquid to the blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Return to the dutch oven and add remaining ingredients.
Cook several minutes till desires consistency.
Serve with pepper strips and sourcream.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Boil turkey giblets in water.
Put margarine, celery and onions and all seasonings in a large pan; simmer until celery and onions are tender.
Add to bread cubes; remove meat from giblets and chop.
Add to bread cubes and add broth until desired moistness.
Dressing should be plenty moist.
Stuff turkey or bake in baking dish about 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake crust first.

title: jiffy beef and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in oil.
Drain.
Combine beef mix, garlic salt, salt, tomato soup and macaroni and cheese.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes more.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix and heat in a small casserole.
Serve hot with crisp Doritos.

title: kool-aid jelly
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, Sure-Jell and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil again.
Pour immediately into jars.

title: barb's spinach salad
directions: Place greens in a bowl; add chestnuts and bean sprouts.
Top with bacon that has been crumbled and eggs.
Eggs should be halved or quartered.

title: cheese delight salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and salt until clear.
Add jello; when dissolved, add 2 cups water.
When almost set, add cheese and whipped cream.
Let set until firm.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in 2 cups boiling water. Add rest of ingredients, stirring well to mix. Place in refrigerator until set.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat, onions and peppers, then add ingredients, potatoes, etc.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water as desired.
Makes 8 to 10 quarts.

title: pineapple mold *
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water together until Jell-O dissolves. Cool, then add the milk and cottage cheese, drained pineapple, nuts and celery.
Pour into salad mold and let set in refrigerator for 6 hours or more.

title: ground beef and vegetables dinner(this dish is low in calories; serves 3.)
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, green pepper, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Add seasonings and cabbage.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir twice.
Just before serving, sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir in milk.
Stir flour and baking powder together.
Stir into egg mixture.
Chill.
Using 1 tablespoon of dough for each, shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. While warm, roll in powdered sugar again.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onions, green pepper and celery.
I use my electric skillet on fairly slow heat until hamburger is lightly browned and vegetables tender.
While this is cooking, prepare enough regular rice (not Minute), cooked with water so you have at least 1 1/4 cups cooked rice.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients and pat into 2 round pans or 19 1/2 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.

title: shi's spaghetti sauce
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Add peppers and onions and continue to cook until onions and peppers are tender.
Place beef, onions and peppers into crock-pot.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cook overnight on low temperature.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water if necessary, depending on desired thickness.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a medium saucepan, using medium heat. When melted, add the condensed milk.
Stir in salt, vanilla extract and walnuts.
Set aside.

title: ruth's orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water. Set aside and cool. Whip the mayonnaise with a mixer or blender and stir in milk, mixing well. Add other ingredients, stirring only, and refrigerate.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place each chicken breast on a cutting surface and hold firmly with the flat of your hand.
Use a sharp knife, held parallel; cut breast into 2 thin slices.
Pat dry and rub poultry seasoning into each slice.
Preheat a 3-quart saucepan.
When the pan is hot to the touch, add the oil and heat.
Add chicken and saute over medium-high heat until lightly browned, about 1 minute on each side, making sure it is cooked through.
Remove chicken to a platter and keep warm.
Deglaze pan by adding wine and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; add parsley.
Pour sauce over chicken and serve immediately.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix salt with cabbage.
Let stand 1 hour.
While cabbage is standing, make dressing.
Squeeze out excess liquid from cabbage; add carrot and pepper.
Pour dressing over slaw.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: sugar-free orange fluff
directions: Fold all ingredients together in bowl.	Transfer into serving bowl.
Chill 20 minutes before serving.

title: tomatoes with green onions and olives
directions: Core the tomatoes and thinly slice; overlap the slices on a serving plate.
Drain and chop the olives.
Combine olives and the green onions, then add the oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon roll aparts
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl.
Separate biscuits and roll in the sugar mixture.
Place biscuits in ungreased Bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and boil until blended.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry torte cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; stir in nuts, dates, cranberries and orange rind.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to fruit mix. Stir until blended.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Punch small holes in top of cake and drizzle on glaze.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples. Place in 8 x 8 x 2 pan. Mix water and lemon juice, then pour over apples. Mix sugar, flour, oats and spices. Add margarine to dry mixture. Mix until crumbly. Sprinkle mixture evenly over apples. Bake at 350° until apples are tender and topping is slightly brown, about 40 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Then add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well with the creamed mixture.
Chill in icebox for at least an hour.

title: hot punch
directions: Heat on stove; serve warm.

title: alaska baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
1st half baking time covered; 2nd half baking time uncovered.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Drain pineapple and reserve syrup.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot cooked pork.
Let stand 10 minutes; add pineapple, green pepper and onion.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: classic quiche lorraine
directions: Sift together flour and salt; cut in shortening until consistency of meal.
Cut in butter until consistency of small peas.
Stir in cold water and blend lightly, just until dough holds together and can be rolled into a ball.
Roll out to fit a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish.
Microwave on High for about 4 to 6 minutes, rotating dish frequently and pricking any large air bubbles that form with a fork.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems and dice.
Mix in mayonnaise and Bac*Os bits.
Fill mushroom caps with the mixture.
Arrange filled mushrooms on cookie sheet and bake for 4 to 8 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.
Nuts can be put on top if wanted.
Let cool, then put marshmallows on top.
Bake until marshmallows are melted.
This is an old recipe from my great-aunt Vernon.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: *Bring water to boil in large kettle.
Add salt.
Add macaroni.
Stir and bring to full rolling boil on high heat.
Stir constantly and boil for 2 minutes on high, then cover pan.
Remove from heat.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
There's no boiling over. Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over low heat.
In a bowl, stir cocoa and sugar together.
Stir in melted butter. Add eggs and vanilla and stir again. Add flour and salt.
Mix until smooth. Add walnuts and stir again.
Pour into baking pan and spread evenly. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides. Cool completely before cutting.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin
and sugar in hot water and cool.
Add juices.
Chill and add ginger ale just before serving.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour cherries into a baking dish.
Mix other ingredients together with enough milk to make a medium batter.
Pour over cherries and bake at 350° until light brown or inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing, melted margarine and chicken broth together and spread 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: afternoon tea cakes(sputniks)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Keep turning.
Shake in bag with a little sugar.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: mom's vegetable salad
directions: Add oil to water and cook macaroni.
Drain and set aside.
Let cool.
You can run cold water over macaroni to cool.
Cut up vegetables very small.
Mix all ingredients together.
The longer this sits, the better flavor it has.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and shape into 12 meatballs. Brown in oil in skillet.
Remove excess fat.
Combine tomato sauce, molasses, vinegar and seasoned salt.
Pour over meatballs. Simmer on low for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: In large saucepan, saute beef with 1/4 cup of beef stock on low heat until lightly browned.
Add onions, carrots, celery, bay leaf, remaining stock and wine.
Bring to gentle boil and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook for another five minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Also great as is with bread as a complement.

title: boston brown bread(traditional with baked beans)
directions: Sift all-purpose flour with baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in cornmeal and whole wheat flour.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Divide batter among 4 greased and floured 1 pound food cans.
Cover tightly with foil.
Place on rack in deep kettle; pour in 1-inch boiling water.
Cover kettle and steam for
3 hours; add more boiling water if needed.
Uncover cans and place in 450° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove bread from cans.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.
Makes 4 loaves; also good with cream cheese.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour and pineapple on stove until thick.
Let it cool.
Peel and cut up apples into cubes.
Pour cooled mixture over the apples.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Serve chilled.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef well and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook approximately 45 minutes.
Servings: 8.

title: chocolate brownie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat into batter.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda separately.
Mix flour mixture into batter.
Add milk, chips and nuts last.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar in large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Use remaining M&M's to decorate tops of cookies before baking.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Place flat in baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 80 walnut-sized balls for appetizers.

title: ham croquettes
directions: Melt margarine; stir in flour.
Add milk.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add ham, onion, horseradish and mustard. Refrigerate for 30 minutes or longer.
Shape in ball.
Roll in crumbs, then into beaten eggs and then back in the crumbs.
Cook in hot oil (375°) until brown, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Mix zucchini, oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nuts and flour.
Hand mix for 2 minutes.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: best hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine in the top of a double boiler.
Mix in confectioners sugar once margarine is melted.
Add evaporated milk; blend until all lumps are gone.
Drop the squares of chocolate into the pan; cover and cook over simmering water for 30 minutes.
Do not stir until the 30 minutes is up.
Remove from heat; mix with wire whisk or fork until smooth.
May be refrigerated and reheated.

title: zucchini chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream eggs, oil, applesauce and zucchini.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Core apples and cut into chunks, leaving the peeling on.
Add pineapple chunks and 1 tablespoon mayonnaise.
Set in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Add peanuts and stir to mix.
(Peanuts will become soggy after a few hours.)

title: southern barbecued ribs
directions: Set power select at High on your microwave.
In oblong baking dish, combine ingredients.
Heat, covered, for 10 minutes.
Set power select on Low.
Heat, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until ribs are tender, stirring once.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop from a teaspoon into hot deep fat.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix together in order given.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. One pie crust needed.

title: quiche (ham and eggs)
directions: Bake pie shell at 425° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Stuff pie shell with ham and cheese.
After mixing all other ingredients, pour over ham and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes or until fork comes out clean when tested.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
In large skillet, saut garlic in olive oil until slightly browned.
Add vegetables and stir.
Saute for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Toss vegetables and parsley with drained pasta. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with grated cheese before serving.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: childrens' play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until dough pulls away from sides of pan. Knead 1 minute.
Store in a plastic bag in refrigerator when not in use.

title: decadent dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Add bread crumbs, Cream of Wheat, baking powder and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and break the cake into chunks.
Mound layers with whipped cream in between and on top, forming in the shape of a mountain.
Dribble toppings over top.
May garnish with cherries or strawberries.

title: hot weather soup
directions: Blend soup and cream together with egg beaters.
Chill for 1 hour or more before serving.
Good pick up.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fireman stew
directions: Cut up stew beef and place in bottom of casserole dish (do not brown).
Add French onion soup and tomato soup.
Stir.
Add sliced carrots, turnip, onions and potatoes.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn oven off and keep casserole in oven for another 45 minutes.
Do not take cover off during this 45 minute time.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Place carrot strips in a buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with brown sugar and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Let batter stand 5 minutes.
Carefully drop batter by level tablespoons into deep hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and cut onion and avocados into 1-inch pieces.
Put all ingredients into blender and blend until smooth.
Serve with corn chips or tostados.
Yields 2 cups.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Boil potatoes just until they start to get tender.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add milk, soups, salt and pepper.
Heat until creamy. Carefully add to drained potatoes.
Fold until potatoes are well covered.
Place in small casserole dish (sprayed with cooking spray).
Bake at 350° until sauce has thickened and potatoes are tender.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together to smooth batter.
Pour batter into dish with butter. Pour fruit into center of mixture (do not stir in).
Bake at 450° until top is covered and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove bones.
Cook noodles for 8 minutes. Drain and rinse with very hot water.
Add cheese immediately, stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms, soup and onion.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or more.
Yields 18 servings.

title: pasta primavera marinara
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and put in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, warm marinara sauce, stirring constantly.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet coated with cooking spray, add the garlic; saut 1 or 2 minutes.
Add broccoli, carrot and pepper; saut until tender.
Add to the marinara sauce. Mix well.
Then add to the pasta; mix well. Garnish with cheese.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: holiday bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, raisins and cherries just as you would for normal bread making.
Just before adding last cup of flour, add remaining ingredients and complete kneading.
Place in greased bowl and let rise twice.
Make into loaves.
Let rise and bake 40 to 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Ice with powdered sugar and sprinkle with nuts.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix and form together. Roll in pecans.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl combine mayonnaise, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add potatoes, celery, onion and eggs; toss to coat well. Cover, chill to blend flavors.

title: johnny appleseed pie
directions: Combine the 1/3 cup sugar and the cinnamon; mix with apples. Turn into pie shell.
Top with chocolate chips.
In small bowl, combine the Bisquick and the 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle evenly over pie.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.
If pastry browns too quickly, cap loosely with foil during last 5 to 10 minutes of baking.

title: oatmeal dinner rolls
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil; add oats and butter. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Remove from the heat; cool to lukewarm. In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add the oat mixture, sugars, salt and 4 c. of flour; beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6-8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch dough down; allow to rest for 10 minutes. Shape into 18 balls. Place in two greased 9 inch round baking pans. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan to wire racks.

title: supper on a bread slice
directions: Combine ingredients.
(Cracker meal can be hand crumbled saltine crackers.)
Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread meat mixture evenly over top surface of bread.
Wrap heavy-duty foil around crust side of each half, leaving top uncovered.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with strips of cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
To serve, cut slices diagonally.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Take pan off heat and put in soda and vanilla.
Slowly pour over popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Mix all together. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour the mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake the pie at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake for 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: easy yummy potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator. Serve with chips or use on tossed salad or with raw vegetables.

title: spaghetti sauce of three meats
directions: Brown meat pieces in hot fat with the sliced onion and garlic. Add the strained tomatoes and paste. Stir in the seasonings and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add lemon juice to taste.
Cook spaghetti.
Heat the meatballs.
Remove meat from sauce and slice. Combine sauce, meat and meatballs.
Serve.
Freezes well.
Serves 12.

title: ramen salad
directions: Combine ingredients, adding Ramen noodles just before serving.

title: one pan chicken and stuffing
directions: Any cream soup can be substituted.
Can also substitute pork for chicken.

title: turkey chili
directions: In Dutch oven, melt margarine, add onions and garlic.
Saute until onions are translucent.

Add ground turkey, chili powder, cumin, salt, oregano, paprika, peppers, beef broth and tomatoes. Simmer 30 minutes.	Add kidney beans and simmer 10 minutes more. (Chili improves in flavor if refrigerated for a day then reheated.) 10 Servings, 206 calories per serving, 6 grams fat, 58 mg cholesterol, 648 mg sodium.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks.
Mix yolks with all other ingredients. Fill whites using pastry tube.
Garnish with paprika/parsley flakes and tiny pimento pieces for a nice "holly" effect at Christmastime.

title: chicken-crescent almondine
directions: Cook first seven ingredients in saucepan until hot and bubbly. Pour into a 12 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch casserole or baking dish. Separate crescent roll dough in rectangles.
Place over hot mixture.
Combine shredded cheese and slivered almonds and sprinkle over dough.
Cover with 2 to 4 tablespoons of melted butter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375° until golden brown. Serve at once.
(This reheats well.)

title: hurry up cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fast chocolate-pecan fudge
directions: Microwave butter in 2-quart micro-proof bowl at High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Add cocoa.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Blend well (mixture wil be dry and crumbly).
Stir in evaporated milk. Microwave at High (100%) for 1 minute; stir.
Microwave an additional 1 minute or until mixture is hot.
Stir mixture until smooth; add pecans.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Cover; chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: homemade bread in coffee cans
directions: Mix; knead and let rise until double in size.
Put into greased coffee cans (13 ounce).
Let rise until double.
Bake in warm preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until brown on top. Makes 3.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in cast-iron skillet. Cook broccoli as stated on package and drain. Add all ingredients in bowl and mix well. Pour back into skillet. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done. Serve with pinto beans!

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Melt butter and add to dry ingredients until crumbly. Blend egg, milk and vanilla together and add to batter.
Put 3/4 of batter in baking pan.
Put it in with floured hands.
Add pie filling.
Take remaining batter and roll out on floured board. Cut in strips to make lattice top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Cut up beef finely with scissors. Cut tops of green onions into bowl with scissors. Add cream cheese, Accent and garlic salt. Add half of the dried beef. Roll into a ball. Roll the ball in the remaining dried beef. Serve with crackers.

title: red hot jello salad
directions: Dissolve red hot candies in water.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add applesauce.
Pour into mold or dish and refrigerate until firm.
Really good with ham.

title: savory beef stew
directions: In preheated electric skillet at 325°, brown beef in melted fat.
Add seasonings and bouillon.
Reduce heat to 200°; cover and cook 35 minutes.
Add carrots and onions; cook an additional 25 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and steam 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bean soup
directions: *Use at least 7 varieties of beans from your field, co-op or health food store.
Choose Great Northern, navy, black, garbanzo, green split peas, pinto and red beans.

title: taco salad
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper until beef is brown. Stir in seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until soft.
Remove from pot.
Add hamburger and brown.
Return the onion mixture to the pot and add salt, chili powder, tomatoes and beans.
Cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: kathleen's mushroom smothered quail
directions: Brown quail quickly in skillet with small amount of oil. Remove quail and place into covered casserole. Add onion and celery to skillet and simmer until tender.
Add chopped mushroom stems and simmer until tender.
Add crumbled bacon into skillet and cook slightly, then add mushroom caps.
Cool slightly.
Mix flour with water and chicken bouillon in a covered jar and shake until flour is well blended, then pour mixture into skillet of simmered vegetables.
Cook until thickened over medium heat.
Pour over quail in casserole dish.
Cover and place in oven. Bake at 350° for 1 minute, then lower temperature to 300° and continue to cook for 30 minutes longer.
Serve with rice pilaf or long grain and wild rice mix.

title: praline butter cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve granulated sugar in 1/3 cup water over moderate heat, stirring.

Bring the mixture to a boil. Continue boiling, undisturbed, until it begins to turn golden. Boil the syrup, swirling the pan, until it turns a deep caramel; stir in the pecans and pour mixture immediately onto foil, spreading the pecans into a single layer. Let the praline cool completely.
Peel off the foil, discarding it; break the praline into pieces, and in a food processor, grind it coarse.

title: applesauce squares
directions: Mix butter and sugar well.
Heat applesauce until warm; add soda to applesauce, stirring well.
Add this mixture to butter-sugar mixture.
Add egg, vanilla and milk; mix well.
Blend in flour, spices and raisins.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Ice with powdered sugar-water mixture.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on box.
Crumble one layer on bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare 1 box instant pudding.
Pour it over cake.
Spread pie filling and pineapple over pudding, then spread Cool Whip.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Finish with maraschino cherries.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls. Bake on a cookie sheet until golden brown or done.

title: pizza
directions: Soften yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
In mixing bowl, pour hot water over salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm and add yeast.
Stir.
Add flour, mixing until smooth.
Knead 12 strokes; divide and press out on two 12-inch pizza pans.
(A small amount of oil on the pan helps.)
Run pepperoni through food processor until very fine; mix with garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce and oregano.
Spread sauce on pizza dough, dividing evenly.
Add any toppings you like, then cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans; put in large bowl.
Add onions; dissolve sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and oil.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken-n-cornbread dressing with giblet gravy
directions: Cook hen until tender in salted water in a large cooker so there will be plenty of broth.

title: taco pie
directions: Place in pie pan in order given. Slice the cream cheese to put over chili.
Use 1 or 2 peppers depending on how hot or spicy you like your food.
Bake at 375° until heated all the way through (20 to 30 minutes). Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add the rest of ingredients; stir and knead well.
Store in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.
Doesn't crumble a lot.

title: potatoes beef
directions: Roll in balls and brown about 30 minutes at 350°.
Slice potatoes round, thin sliced.
Place over meat balls.
Add 1 can celery soup and 1/2 can water.
Cook in covered dish for 1/2 hour at 300°.

title: chinese cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey; drain and return to pan.
Add seasoning from Ramen noodles to water and pour into pan.
Pack noodles into water/ground beef mixture.
Layer green onions, bell pepper and cabbage.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry o cream cheese pie
directions: Let
cream cheese soften to room temperature, whip until fluffy.
Gradually
add
the
milk, beating until well blended. Add
lemon
juice
and vanilla, blending well.
Pour into crumb crust,
chill 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish top of pie with cherry pie filling or glaze.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Fold in eggs, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Add salt and flavorings.
Beat until very smooth.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour.
The first 30 minutes, bake at 325°.
Second 30 minutes, bake at 350°.

title: mrs. hitler's grit casserole
directions: To the boiling water, add the grits and salt and cook until done.
Melt together the margarine and the cheese stick.
Add to the grits.
Beat 2 eggs in a cup and finish filling cup with milk. Add to grits.
Pour mixture into a buttered dish; cover with crushed cornflakes and bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: keshia's pinto beans
directions: Pick and clean beans.
Soak beans in water overnight. Discard soaking water.
Using fresh water, cover beans and cook (simmer) until water is almost gone.
Repeat process until beans are tender.
Add a stick of butter and bouillon, and stir.
Must be served with cornbread, milk, and chopped onion.

title: dump cake
directions: Take a 13 x 9-inch pan, put in pie fillings, cover with cake mix and top with butter.
Can be topped with chopped walnuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes plus, until brown and bubbly.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown onions. Mix all ingredients in onions. Stir. Pour over 2 pounds chipped ham. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen pineapple delight
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk; cool.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Put 1/2 of crumbs on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour on pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and freeze.

title: chicken and avocado sandwiches
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, cut each avocado lengthwise in half. Remove seed and peel. Chop avocados.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Cook in small amount of water until soft.
Combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add alternate layers of eggplant, milk, mixture, crumbs, grated cheese and butter in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Sift flour in large mixing bowl.
Add gumdrops, coconut, nuts, oatmeal, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs, sugar and shortening.
Mix with mixture.
Work together with hands.
Pinch off in little balls and bake in 350° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zippy squash casserole
directions: Wash squash thoroughly.
Trim off ends.
Place in boiling water and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash. Combine next 7 ingredients; add squash, stirring well.
Spoon squash mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole (sprayed with Pam). Sprinkle bread crumbs over squash mixture, then sprinkle with Molly McButter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a covered bowl in the refrigerator until ready to serve. The flavors will blend better if the salad is made one day, stored in the refrigerator overnight and then served the next day. If the salad is stored overnight, the macaroni may soak up your mayonnaise and dry out your salad. If this happens simply add a small amount of mayonnaise to moisten your salad.
Serves 8.

title: transparent pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine sugar, margarine, egg yolks, flour, vanilla and evaporated milk in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May use egg whites for meringue.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Heat cranberry juice to boiling.
Add raspberry Jell-O and cranberry sauce.
Stir well and refrigerate until set.
Remove from refrigerator and stir until fluffy.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked french toast
directions: Cut the French bread into slices and place in a greased 9x13 inch pan.
In bowl, beat eggs, sugar and cinnamon; stir in milk and mix well.
Pour over the French bread; cover pan with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp croquette
directions: While boiling potatoes, chop onion and cook shrimp.
Put mashed potatoes in bowl and mix with other ingredients.
Form into balls and dip in mixture of white sauce (flour and water) and bread crumbs.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Serve with salad of choice.

title: "grey's" strawberry pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients well and press in a pie pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool before putting in the filling.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add flour and oatmeal.
May also add 1 cup of pecans or 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Cook for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Remove 6 tablespoons juice from strawberries and set aside. Put sugar, lemon juice, strawberries and egg whites into a bowl. Beat on high speed for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla.
Pour mixture into crust and freeze for about 8 hours.

title: bacon squares
directions: Slice bread.
Cut into quarters.
Spread bacon mixture on bread.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove when cheese is melted.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Smash 20 Oreos with their cream centers and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powder from the 3 boxes of pudding with the milk and vanilla ice cream by hand.
Pour over cookies.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle 10 more crushed Oreos over the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight.
Tastes better when left overnight.
Serve.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with favorite pie filling; cherry, blueberry, peach, etc.

title: barbecued pork tenderloin
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine garlic and olive oil.
Add Worcestershire sauce and stir.
Add soy sauce and teriyaki sauce and mix well.
Add fresh ground pepper to taste.
Lay pork tenderloins in a large glass baking dish.
Pour the marinade over the tenderloins.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 1 to 6 hours. Prepare grill (coals or gas grill).
Grill pork tenderloins until desired degree of doneness.
Slice and serve.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Saute meat.
Stir in flour, pepper and thyme.
Pour in broth and wine.
Cover and cook at 225° to 350° for 2 hours.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Add equal parts of broth and wine as needed.
Cook until meat is tender.
Good over wild rice or noodles.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut onion and pepper in slices and mix with carrots.
Combine all ingredients. Pour marinade over vegetables.
Cover and marinate 12 hours or more.
Drain and serve.
Serves 10.

title: cream puffs
directions: Pour boiling water over butter in pan.
Heat until butter melts.
Add flour all at once.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat. Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating to a smooth paste after each one.
Beat until smooth and velvety.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 30 to 40 minutes longer.
When cooked, slice off tops and fill with filling, whipped cream, ice cream, hot creamed chicken or any creamed fish and replace tops.
Makes 7 to 8.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound
chicken	breasts
until	thin.
Add
slice of cheese and
slice
of ham to center of each chicken breast. Roll up each and secure with toothpicks.
Dip into beaten egg, then
into bread
crumbs.
Repeat
twice.
Place into lightly greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Serves 4.

title: macaroni and cheese(from mary mac's tea room)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil macaroni pieces in water for 6 minutes.
Drain in colander; rinse well under running water to remove starch.
Beat 3 eggs.
Add following ingredients and mix well together:
2 cups milk, 1/4 cup evaporated milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon white pepper, dash of Tabasco sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons melted margarine and 2 cups grated cheese.
Add macaroni and pour into 1-quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until soft as custard.

title: rumanian veal and vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 350 F.
Slice veal into 1 inch strips.
In nonstick baking dish, place sliced veal, seasoned with pepper and set aside.

title: dropped chocolate cookies with peanut butter chips(student favorite)
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add peanut butter chips, stirring by hand.
Place teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cookies are soft, and will "drop" when taken from the oven.
Cook about a minute. Remove and cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: no cook mint patties
directions: In mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Dust hands and bread board with powdered sugar to prevent sticking.
Shape dough into a roll about 1/2 inch in diameter.
Cut into slices 1/2 inch thick. Place slices on wax paper.
Press down edges with a fork.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour before serving.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: seven layer bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and set in oven to melt butter.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in pan in order given.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch bars.
Makes 39 bars.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a rolling boil. Cook rapidly for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly (mixture scorches easily).
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate morsels and add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour quickly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: cheesy chicken souffle
directions: Butter 9 inch baking dish, line bottom with 4 slices bread. Cover with sliced chicken.
Spread with mayonnaise and sprinkle with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Top with remaining 4 slices of buttered bread.

title: cressic greens
directions: Wash greens and cut off roots.
Place greens in large pot with water.
Boil until tender.
Drain off water.
Cook ham or bacon trimmings in pan until fat has cooked out.
Place drained grease into fat and mix with drippings and salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a large pot, add olive oil and next four (4) ingredients. Saute; when onions turn clear, add tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and wine to remove bitterness of tomatoes. (Wine is optional.)
After tomatoes are cooked, add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: swiss brunch casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage in pan and drain.
Mix with mustard and spread over bread. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 40 minutes.
Remove cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spiced applesauce bread
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk.
Mix well, add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Whatever you want.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
If you want you can combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cooks quicker in 2 pans.
You can put in one pan if you want.
Bake until done.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: southern lemon pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, meal, butter, whole egg and 3 yolks; beat 1 minute.
Add pineapple-orange juice and water.
Cook until thick.
(This can be done in microwave for 5 minutes, stirring once.)
Slowly add lemon juice.
Cook 1 minute longer. Add to cooked pastry shell.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and season with salt and pepper.
Add onion to meat mixture and brown; drain.
Mix in large can of pork and beans and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Mix until just blended after each addition.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: chocolate nut zucchini cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot, not boiling water; let cool.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl of electric mixer beat eggs at high speed until thick and light.
Gradually add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add oil and cooled chocolate; beat until well blended.
At low speed, add sifted dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add grated zucchini and nuts, stirring with a wooden spoon until well mixed.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cake can be dusted with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: easy cheese lemon bars
directions: Mix with fork the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch or 10 x 15-inch pan, grease bottom only.
Blend frosting and cream cheese (reserve 1/2 cup for topping).
Add 2 eggs and beat 2 to 5 minutes.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and spread with 1/2 cup of the reserved frosting mixture.
Cut in squares.

title: divinity pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites on high until frothy; gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff peaks form. Fold in with a spatula the finely crushed Ritz crackers, then the pecans.
(Do not beat in with beaters).
Pour pie mixture in buttered pie plate and bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: louisiana community coffee spice cake
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices together. Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add ingredients and coffee alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition. Fold in pecans.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: punch for 50
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shortly before serving add ginger ale.

title: potato soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Combine broth, onion, potatoes, pepper and seasoned salt.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until tender (about 30 to 40 minutes). Melt butter.
Mix with flour and add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Combine the two mixtures and simmer until warm.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup over the top and cover with crushed corn flakes.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When it starts to bubble, cook 5 minutes more.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients except English muffins.
Use beater for beating, if necessary.
Cut each muffin into quarters.
Spread mixture on quarters.
Put pieces on trays; freeze at least 30 minutes.
(May be kept frozen for weeks.)
Just before serving, put pieces on tray under broiler.
Broil a few minutes until they puff up bubbly and slightly golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix together soup, corn and ground beef and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linguini salad
directions: Boil macaroni.
Drain and rinse well.
All vegetables may be increased or decreased, substituted or deleted to your liking. Add 1/2 of Wish-Bone dressing to cooked noodles.
Next, add Salad Supreme to your taste.
Add all vegetables and pepperoni and mix well.
Let sit overnight or 4 or more hours in fridge.
Add more dressing and the Mozzarella cheese before serving.

title: orange pineapple cream salad
directions: Drain pineapple into Jell-O and bring to a boil.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Whip until creamy.
Add pineapple and pecans. Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Fix stuffing as indicated on box.
Combine cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup with 2 cans of broth from cooked chicken.
Tear or cut chicken up and layer bottom of casserole with chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken. Layer with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice krispies peanut butter bars
directions: Stir and bring to boil syrup and sugar; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir in Rice Krispies. Pat into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, onion powder, and minced garlic.
Combine beef, salsa, sour cream and 2 cups cheese in slow cooker.
Cover.
Heat on low for 2 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemony green beans
directions: Season and cook green beans.
Slice and separate onions into rings.
Saute rings in butter.
Add lemon juice and brown sugar to beans.
Cook until heated.
Drain cooked beans and place in serving dish.
Pour onion mixture over beans and serve.

title: dirty rice(la style)
directions: Cook meat until it falls apart.
Cook onion with meat.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Add rice.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Pop the corn; sprinkle with salt.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cut marshmallows in quarters.
Alternate layers of popcorn and marshmallows in skillet.
Cover; heat slowly until marshmallows are partially melted.
Mix well; form into balls.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in 1/4-inch slices and place on buttered baking dish.
Add cinnamon and water.
Work sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples and bake at 340° uncovered for about 40 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: milk sausage gravy
directions: Fry sausage in cast-iron skillet.
Remove sausage patties and reserve 1/4 cup drippings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook whole sweet potatoes in boiling water 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: party chicken
directions: Separate beef slices and place in bottom of an 8-inch square casserole.
Wrap bacon around chicken breast and place on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: apple tortilla dessert
directions: Put approximately 1 to 2 tablespoons pie filling in each tortilla.
Roll and arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil sugar, water and margarine.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil during the first 30 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients for 1 minute, then cool 1 minute. Add remainder of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: baked pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Place sauerkraut in bottom of casserole. Top with seasoned pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove cover and bake for 20 minutes longer or until pork chops are brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut a thin slice off the stem end of the peppers.
Remove and discard the seeds.
In a 1 1/2-quart nonmetal casserole, combine onion and ground beef.
Place in microwave oven and cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until the onion becomes transparent and beef is slightly browned.
Add rice, tomato sauce, celery salt and pepper; mix well.
Stuff peppers with mixture and place on baking sheet.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on Medium-high for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: michelle's chicken bake
directions: Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole the chicken breasts until done. Debone and cut into chunks.
Layer chicken and Stove Top dressing (cooked) in casserole.
Pour over 2 cups of chicken gravy on top. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Wash the grapefruit and cut in half crosswise.
Loosen grapefruit sections around outer edge and between segments with a grapefruit knife.
Place a cherry in the middle and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Broil for a few minutes until the sugar melts and is bubbly.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown beef in oil; add onions and brown.
Add all other ingredients and cook for several hours.

title: reception salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and reserved pineapple juice. Add water to it to make 1 cup, if needed.
Refrigerate.
When partially set, mash the cheese into it with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add the whipped cream last.
Let chill until firm.

title: easy freezer pickles
directions: In large bowl, place cucumbers, onions and green pepper.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables and mix well to coat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Divide into pint or quart freezer boxes and freeze until ready to use.

title: spice crumb apple pie
directions: Mix and sift 2 c. flour and the salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is coarse like cornmeal.
Divide in half.
Sprinkle water over half of mixture and blend only until moistened and crumbly. Turn out on a pastry board and roll lightly.
Line an 8 inch pie pan and flute the edges.
To remaining portion of crumbs add 1/4 c. sugar, 1 1/2 tsp cinnamon and 1/2 tsp nutmeg.
Set aside.
Mix remaining sugar, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and flour together.
Sprinkle some on unbaked crust.
Alternate layers of apples and crumbs.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake in a 425° oven 50 to 55 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake scrubbed and pricked potatoes for 1 hour.
Cut potatoes in half and scoop out center into bowl with butter.
Save the shells.
Mash potatoes until light and fluffy. Add cream, cheese, chives, bacon bits and season to taste.
Fill hollowed out shells with potato mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or microwave 5 minutes.

title: whole wheat blueberry pancakes
directions: Optional: Can add 1/4 cup finely chopped walnuts.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oil and eggs; stir until well moistened.
Do not beat.
Add pineapple (juice and all), bananas, pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into large 11 x 14-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and canning salt in 9-quarts of ice cold water.
Let stand for 3 hours; drain.
Pack cucumbers and onions in jars.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Pour over cucumbers, then bathe in boiling water; quarts for 15 minutes or pints for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spread 1 cup of sauce, arrange a layer of lasagna, top with sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Repeat, gently pressing pieces into cheese mixture.
End with a final layer of lasagna, pour remaining sauce over, make sure all lasagna is covered with sauce, top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until lightly brown and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: banana poppy seed muffins
directions: Puree bananas in blender (one cup).
In a medium bowl, mix bananas, eggs, sugar, oil and orange peel until well blended.
In a large bowl, combine flour, poppy seed, baking powder and salt. Stir banana mixture into flour mixture until evenly moistened. Spoon batter into greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.
Top with citrus glaze when warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Steam zucchini slices until tender.
Add orange slices, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with pecans and serve.
Serves 4, 60 calories per serving.

title: slippery chicken pot pie
directions: Chicken should be cooked 1 to 2 days before pot pie is needed. In medium bowl, mix all flour, Crisco and enough cold water to form dough ball.
Roll out dough (fairly thin) and cut in 2 x 2-inch wedges.
Allow wedges to dry on wax paper for 1/2 hour. (Note:
Can also be done 1 to 2 hours before hand.)
In separate medium pan, boil potatoes (peeled and quartered) about 20 minutes. Add one packet of seasoning.
Remove fat from broth and place broth in large pan on low heat.
Bring broth to a boil; add flavor packets and deboned chicken.
Place each dough wedge slowly in boiling broth.
Lower heat to medium.
Pour potatoes and remaining water into the broth, allowing them to finish cooking with dough. Add salt and pepper.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes and serve hot with toast or rolls.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and pineapple.
Add chunk pineapple.
Add pudding and mix well.
Mix Cool Whip with mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: teddy's favorite greens
directions: Anytime up to a day ahead, shallow blanch the greens as follows.
Bring 2 quarts water to boil in a stockpot or large soup kettle.
Add salt and greens; stir until wilted.
Cover and cook 7 minutes; drain in colander and rinse with cold water.
Take a handful; squeeze all the water out.
Transfer to a cutting board. Repeat until all greens are squeezed.
Chop coarsely.
Greens can be refrigerated until ready to saute.

title: kids fun meat snack
directions: Put the cheese on the meat.
Roll up and put in microwave for 2 minutes (oven for 1 minute).
Serve.

title: white chili
directions: Wash beans; place in kettle, cover and soak for 24 hours. Drain.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Cover with 5 cups water and cook for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Add enough additional broth to make 10 cups total.
Strain broth and add beans, onions, celery, cumin, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaves. Bring to boil.
Add 2 to 3 cups of the cooked chicken, cut into small pieces and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours until beans are tender.
Add milk to flour and add to kettle.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in apples with water.
Pour into tube pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 250° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: pound cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and punch a hole in the center and fill with jelly. Bake at 225° or 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Beat margarine until creamy; add sugars and beat until fluffy. Stir in vanilla and eggs.
Stir in soaked oats.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamy mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: indian corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 425° to 450°, about 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best when made ahead, allowing flavors to gently blend.
Serve with assorted vegetable sticks.

title: tasty rice dish
directions: Melt oleo, saute onion and parsley with rice.
Add liquid, then garlic and tomato paste.
Stir with a fork.
Cook slow.
Add more water, if needed.
Cook until rice is tender.
This should be a moist rice, but not soupy.
Add grated cheese at the end. Additional cheese may be added on each serving.

title: tomato and beef casserole(serves 6)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Combine meatballs and remaining ingredients except bell pepper.
Heat over medium-low heat until boiling; reduce heat. Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pepper; cook an additional 10 minutes or until meatballs are no longer pink. Serve over rice if desired.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla and butter, in saucepan. Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick (just to a boil). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions;
fill bottom of casserole; cover with soup.	Layer Tater Tots on top.
Cover with grated cheese. Bake until Tater Tots are done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Shape into loaf and place in an oblong pan.
Spread tomato paste over top of loaf.
Add water to rest of sauce in can, mix up and pour around loaf in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked flounder
directions: Spray Pam on bottom of pan. Lay filets in pan. Crush Ritz crackers over fish. Put small slices of butter over crackers. Add lemon juice to pan. Bake in oven 25 minutes at 450°.

title: french bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water (115°).
Add 6 cups flour and stir until well mixed.
Turn mixture out onto well floured counter top and work in flour as dough is kneaded.
Knead for 10 minutes until mixture is smooth and elastic and no longer sticky.
(Add flour a 1/2 cup at a time).
Place in greased bowl to rise until double in bulk.
Cover with damp towel while rising.
Divide dough in four equal portions and place in French bread pans.
Let rise until double in bulk again.
Cook in 375° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes until brown and crusty.
Loaves should sound hollow when tapped.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together in a saucepan.
Heat to a full rolling boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal.
Stir.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and allow to set.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: In 3 to 4-quart shallow, glass bowl, layer first five ingredients in order given.
Spread evenly with mayonnaise. Sprinkle the next 4 ingredients on top of mayonnaise.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, crumble bacon on top. Sprinkle with eggs and tomato wedges.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place wings in baking pan.
Combine sauce and dry ingredients in a saucepan and bring to
a simmer for five minutes.
Pour over wings and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Tie spices loosely in cheesecloth bag.
Mix all ingredients except lemon peel and bring to a boil.
Cool, then remove spice bag.
Reheat and serve very hot.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add small amount to eggs and return to mixture, cooking two minutes.
Cool and add butter and vanilla.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add jello and set aside to cool.
Beat Dream Whip and cream cheese together. Fold in jello mixture.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken with pineapple sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Stir in pineapple, soy sauce, garlic salt, and ginger. Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate with oleo.
Fill two-thirds full of apples. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over apples. In separate bowl mix 1 cup sugar with melted margarine and pecans.
Add flour, egg and salt to mixture.
Mix well.
Spread over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 65 minutes, depending on how hot oven runs, or until golden brown.

title: clair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk; mix well. Fold in frozen topping and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Butter 9 x 13 pan and place layer of graham crackers. Spread 1/2 pudding mix on top of crackers. Place another layer of graham crackers and spread the rest of the pudding mix. Top with another layer of crackers. Pour cooled Chocolate Topping over graham crackers.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: *Note:
I use whole box of chicken Rice-A-Roni.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Gradually add the jam.
(Use a little flour to dredge the fruit.)
Mix soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice with remaining flour and add alternately with the beaten egg whites.
Add the fruit and nuts. Bake in deep, well greased pan or pans in slow oven (250°) about 5 to 6 hours.
(I let my cake stand overnight in the mixing bowl.) Before baking, place a pan of water on rack under where the cake is baking.
Be sure not to let it bake dry.
Makes about 12 pounds cake.

title: church windows
directions: Melt together margarine and chocolate chips in double boiler on low heat.
Partially cool.
Stir marshmallows and chopped nuts into chocolate, coating all.
Sprinkle coconut on wax paper and shape candy into 2 rolls.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
Slice into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: turkey supreme casserole
directions: Mix turkey with sour cream and soup.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Mix melted margarine, broth and stuffing.
Put on top of turkey mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry stuffed pork chops
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1 cup cranberries, breadcrumbs, hot water, butter, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper.
Sprinkle pork chops with garlic salt and fresh ground pepper to taste.
Rub in.
Stuff pockets with cranberry mixture; seal with toothpicks.

title: crock-pot bean soup
directions: Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: 3 chocolate pies
directions: Pour into 3 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken breasts dicola
directions: Coat chicken breasts with 1/2 cup flour, salt and pepper. Place in preheated skillet with oil covering bottom of skillet. Brown both sides, drain oil.
Add 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Sprinkle both sides of breasts with basil and rosemary. Saute both sides for 1/2 minute.
Add wine and saute for 1 minute. Add brown gravy.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken onto serving dish, mix remainder of ingredients left in pan, heat and pour over breasts on serving dish.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Do not drain sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand a few hours or overnight.
This salad keeps well.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Dissolve pudding and jello in boiling water and refrigerate. Stir frequently for approximately 1 hour or until thickened.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 5 hours.

title: mint flickette cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugars, eggs and vanilla. Combine the flour, salt and baking soda; sift and blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in Mint Flickettes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: honey apple jelly
directions: Wash and quarter apples.
Cover with water.
Add lemon juice and simmer until soft.
Drain through jelly bag.
Measure 4 cups juice into kettle and boil 5 minutes.
Add honey and spices.
Boil for 8 minutes more.
Pour into sterilized jelly glasses and seal.

title: callie mae bailey's strawberry cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon and set aside. Cook beef with onion until red leaves meat. Add other ingredients. Crumble bacon. Put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Best refrigerated overnight before serving.
Makes a lot!

title: chicken salad
directions: Use a fork to combine mayonnaise, vinegar and salt in large bowl.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients.
Toss well and refrigerate.
To serve:
Chill platter, place romaine lettuce on platter and pile salad lightly on top.
Serve with nut breads. Serves 6.

title: breakfast tacos
directions: Saute onions.
Add potatoes and eggs.
When eggs are done, add cheese.
Fry tortillas.
Place egg mixture inside and serve.

title: ham cheese logs
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Place cheeses in small mixing bowl; beat until blended.
Beat in deviled ham; stir in olives.
Chill until almost firm.
Shape into two 8-inch logs; roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
In a separate bowl, cream together shortening, vanilla, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients and milk; blend.
Drop batter from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven; top with 1/2 marshmallow and return to oven for 1 minute.
Cool slightly and frost over marshmallow with Chocolate Frosting.

title: pepper jelly(club member: neil h.)
directions: Chop peppers in blender. Add sugar and vinegar. Boil hard for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes. Add Certo and stir well. Pour in jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Use your imagination and add ingredients to your liking. Using blender, add all dry ingredients.
Slowly drizzle olive oil into blender, do not pour olive oil or it will curdle.
This thickens the mayonnaise.
If desired, sprinkle with pumpkin seasoning.

title: quiche
directions: Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and pepper in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over vegetables.
Bake at 400° until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: burgundy salad
directions: Use 1 cup hot water to dissolve Jell-O.
Add juice from the cherries.
Then add wine, pecans and cherries.
Mold and chill.

title: ham and cheese poppy seed sandwiches
directions: Cut top off rolls.
Blend butter, mayonnaise, mustard, onion and poppy seed. Spread on top and bottom of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese. Wrap in foil.
Heat at 400° and cut.
Great for parties!

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Lightly brown rice and cook onion with garlic in drippings until tender.
Add juice, water, pepper and salt.
Cover; simmer 25 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Garnish with bacon and cheese.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: kathy's cheese ball
directions: Set out cream cheese to soften.
Chop beef and onion tops into small pieces.
With your hands, mix all ingredients, except pecans, and form a ball.
Spread pecan chips on wax paper and roll cheese ball over nuts to cover.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: crock-pot mac and cheese
directions: Toss noodles in the 2 tablespoons oil. Add the rest of ingredients; pour into a lightly greased crock-pot. Mix well. Cook on low for 3 hours in crock-pot, stirring every 30 minutes until done.

title: pesto sauce
directions: In
the mixing bowl of a food processor or blender, put the garlic,
salt, basil, pine nuts and olive oil and process until smooth,
scraping down sides one or two times.
Add the cheeses and butter and process very briefly, just to incorporate the cheeses and butter.
Add 2 tablespoons of the boiling water in which pasta cooked.
If sauce is still too thick, add a little more boiling water.
Process for 1 to 2 seconds.
The sauce is now ready for the cooked pasta.
Serves 4 to 6 for 1 pound thin pasta.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Heat bacon in microwave for 20 to 30 seconds and set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate
cheese.
Set sausage and cheese at room temperature for
approximately
hour
to
soften.
Mix cheese and sausage, gradually adding Bisquick mix, until all ingredients are mixed well.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Scald milk and butter together.
Add
to
beaten
eggs, sugar and flour mixture.	Add
vanilla
and
stir.
Pour	into unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle with coconut over top and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine and mix cold water and corn meal.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Add cornmeal mixture, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil.
Partially cover pan; cook slowly for 7 minutes, stirring often.
Line bottom and sides of a greased 2-quart casserole with cooked mush.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to creamy mixture, then add sifted flour.
Pour into long rectangular pan. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let sit awhile.
Real chewy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix chicken (cooked turkey or ground beef may be used), soup, tomatoes and seasonings.
Layer, starting with chicken mixture, then tortillas, then cheese in ovenproof casserole.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with sour cream and a lettuce and tomato salad.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Saute sausage until cooked.
Set aside to cool.
Put eggs, spinach, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and pepper in blender and mix.
Add cooled sausage.
Cook shells in boiling salted water about 15 minutes.
