Fill cooked and cooled shells with about 1 tablespoon of sausage mixture.
Put shells in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then pour Ragu over shells (don't drown them).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and grated Swiss cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
U-uhm good!!

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients except shortening, chili sauce and jelly well.
Shape into balls and brown in shortening (can also bake in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown).
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly over low heat in crock-pot.
Add meatballs and simmer for several hours, stirring occasionally.
Yields approximately 50 meatballs.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender at High speed for 2 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half.
Cut 2 breast halves into 3/4-inch chunks.
Cut remaining 2 halves crosswise in 1/8-inch thick slices.

title: coke cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar with mixer. Add eggs and beat well. Bring the Coke to a boil with cocoa; add vanilla to butter mixture, then add the buttermilk, flour and baking soda. Add marshmallows last. Batter will be thick. Pour into a well sprayed 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish or pan. Bake at 350° until cake tests done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rich bars
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in oatmeal and brown sugar.
Pat mixture in a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shi kum shi(spinach)
directions: Cook the spinach in boiling water, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Cool it and squeeze the water out of the spinach.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Add the spinach to the liquid mixture and marinate it.
Put it in the refrigerator.
Serve it cold.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add flour and egg yolk. Continue mixing.
Lastly, add vanilla and nuts.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Roll in balls, about an inch in size, or make in any shape desired.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook shells according to box directions.
Cut up chicken.
Combine sour cream and soup and divide into 2 equal amounts.
Add chicken to 1/2 of soup mixture. Stuff shells with this mixture and place in baking dish.
Saute onion and mushrooms in chicken broth until tender, then add to remaining soup mixture.
Pour over stuffed shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut into bite size pieces.
Put back into broth.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup, salt and pepper.
Cut 8 to 10 flour tortillas into small pieces and add to boiling broth; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: last supper salad
directions: Chop apples into bite size pieces.
Mix ingredients, along with apples.
Refrigerate for several hours.
(Adjust to taste.)

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Put the cheeses in a 9
x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Add the green chilies on top of the cheese.
Mix flour, eggs and milk. Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand; cut into squares.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine the soup and the milk.
Cut an onion into eighths. Add the frozen chopped broccoli to soup.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook until the broccoli is tender.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Cook spinach and onion according to package directions.
Drain well, pressing out excess liquid.
In a bowl, combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing and butter.
Stir in spinach and muffin mix.
Cover and chill 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls; arrange on cookie sheet.
Cover; chill until serving time (or place in container and freeze).
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes for chilled puffs or 12 to 15 minutes for frozen puffs or until light brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 50 puffs.

title: cherry smores
directions: Place 1 piece of candy on each cracker.
Microwave, 4 crackers at a time, on High for 45 seconds to 1 minutes, until chocolate starts to melt.
Place 1 marshmallow on each cracker.
Microwave 15 to 30 seconds until soft.
Top each with spoonful of cherry filling.
Repeat.
Makes 8 servings.
Try this recipe with other pie filling/toppings; such as raspberry, blueberry, strawberry and peach.

title: low-calorie hash brown casserole
directions: Bake all ingredients at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown. Serves 4 to 6 adults.

title: ray's corn bread
directions: Combine milk in mixing bowl with flour and meal (use enough meal to make batter smooth, not too thick).
Turn into hot skillet.
Drop in hot oil by spoonfuls.
Comes out in pieces.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.	Beat eggs, slightly.
Mix all ingredients together, except potato chips.	Place into a 9 inch x 13 inch pan that has been sprayed with a vegetable spray.	Top with potato chips.	Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Drain and cool the carrots, then slice thinly.
Mix the other vegetables with the carrots.
In a saucepan, mix together the remaining ingredients and boil.
Pour the dressing over the vegetables and chill.
The longer it marinates, the better the taste.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix ingredients.
Set at room temperature for 30 minutes. Then serve or refrigerate.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add milk, water, soda and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and cocoa. Gradually add flour mixture with other ingredients.
Bake approximately 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Place meat in large pot.
Fill pot with water to cover meat. Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours, until very tender.
Remove meat from broth and let broth cool.
Remove meat from bones and tear into bite size strips.
Place broth in refrigerator or freezer to allow fat to come to top.
Remove and discard the fat.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini in salt water until tender.
Cool.
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Scoop out some of the center (not too much). Saute onion and butter, then add scooped zucchini and cook until like paste.
Add sour cream and cheese.
Fill shells.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven fried buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover a baking sheet with foil.
Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in buttermilk and then in
dry mixture.
Place on pan and bake 45 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar together; bring to a boil.
Boil for 7 minutes; stiring constantly.
Grease a 9 X 13 pan; place 1 1/2 c. nuts in bottom.
Pour brown sugar mixture over nuts.
Put chocolate chips on top and let melt.
Spread around and sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Cut while still warm; then chill in cool place.

title: brussels sprouts scallop
directions: Cook frozen Brussels sprouts according to instructions.
While sprouts are cooking, brown bread crumbs in margarine.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in long pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Place spareribs in bottom of crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 6 to 8 hours on low-medium heat.
Serve with crusty rolls.

title: colored bubbles
directions: Dissolve soap in warm water.
Stir in food coloring, if desired.
Put a small amount of bubbles in a can for each child. Blow bubbles with straws.

title: pickled eggs
directions: For one cup of red beet juice, use 1/2 cup of vinegar and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and then heat to slow boil.
Pour juice on eggs.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, cracker crumbs and peanut butter. Roll out into small balls and chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Using toothpick, dip balls into chocolate and paraffin and place on waxed paper to set.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 2 or 3 balls and refrigerate.
Best if mixed a day ahead of time.
Can be frozen if covered tightly.

title: rice pudding pear tart
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes (until lightly browned).
Set aside.
Bring wine and cinnamon to a boil in a 10-inch skillet.
Add pears; reduce heat, cover and poach for 10 minutes.
Turn over; continue until tender.
Remove from wine; set aside.
Combine rice with half and half, sugar, butter and salt in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Add eggs and vanilla; cook 2 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.
Cut lengthwise slits in pears and fan over pudding.
Bake at 350° until pudding is set.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in lemon juice.
Add shrimp and onion. Add mayonnaise to dipping consistency.
Season to taste.
Always serve the next day.
Tastes much better on second day.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine pineapple and coconut.	Add eggs and sugar; mix well. Mix in
flour,
salt
and
baking
soda.
Pour
into
3 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: walrus salad
directions: Wash and cut apples in half and cut out core.
Wash celery and cut into bite size pieces.
Smash walnuts.
Cut apples into bite size pieces and squirt them with lemon juice.
Mix all together.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: In large bowl, coat noodles with oil; drain off excess. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix with noodles; cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 days.
Stir occasionally.
Will keep one week after it's ready to serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Add 2 cups of water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Add crawfish tails or shrimp; simmer over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add salt and cayenne pepper.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup cool water and slowly pour into gravy while stirring. Allow to simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over steamed rice with hot garlic bread.

title: peanut butter rice krispie treats
directions: Boil sugar and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat.
Put in jar of peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in 6 cups of Rice Krispies, slowly.
Mix well.
Put on tinfoil.
Spray foil with Pam or butter foil.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium-high heat.
Drain fat.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into a large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes about 25 servings.
I make this up, divided into meal sized servings and freeze for several ready to thaw meals.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
(Makes about 2 cups.)
Chill and serve!

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt brown sugar and butter in bottom of pan.
Arrange pineapple and cherries to suit yourself.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Margarine makes a tastier cookie and also may need more flour; test by baking one.)

title: preserved children
directions: Take large field, children and dogs.
Add 1 bubbling creek and some of the pebbles.
Mix the children and small dogs together, put them out in the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the creek over the pebbles.
Sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set in bathtub to cool.
Kiss and keep.

title: con queso dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot with green pepper strips, carrot and celery sticks or French bread cubes.
Makes 3 cups.

title: robin's rice
directions: Put rice in a Pyrex bowl.
Add butter to broth and heat on the stove.
When butter is melted, pour over rice.
Bake in 350° oven for between 30 and 40 minutes (watch to see when all liquid is dissolved in the rice) and you are ready to chow down.
Exactly! Comfort food with the stuff you mentioned.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and oil together and add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate cloud fat-free cake
directions: Sift together flour,
cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt into
mixing
bowl.
Stir	until blended.	Add prunes, vanilla, eggs and
milk
and
stir just until blended. Stir water into batter
until	blended.
Pour	batter	into
2 (9-inch) round cake pans
sprayed	with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° 30 to 35 minutes, or until center tests done with wood pick.
Let cakes cool in
pans
minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to cool.
Frost if desired.

title: donut muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine thoroughly oil, 3/4 cup of sugar, egg and milk.
Add liquid ingredients to dry and stir only to combine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Shake muffins out immediately and while hot, dip in melted butter, then remainder of sugar and cinnamon.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain well.
In large mixing bowl, mix ground beef, chili, chili beans and cheese. Crumble up half bag of Fritos in it and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and cover.
Place in oven at 300° until pie is very hot.

title: mandy's crunchy chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Have a grown-up help you cut the chicken into finger-size pieces.
Fill a large, Ziploc bag with potato chips or crackers.
Seal it shut.
Crush the chips or crackers by banging on them with the back of a wooden spoon.
In a small bowl, beat the egg and milk with a fork.
Dip the chicken pieces into the egg mixture, then place them, one piece at a time, into the bag.
Shake each gently to cover with the chips or crackers. Place the coated chicken pieces on an ungreased cookie sheet.
With the help of a parent, place in the oven.
Bake for 10 minutes, then turn over the pieces.
Bake for another 10 minutes. Dip the fingers into barbecue sauce, salsa or your favorite sauce. Serves 2.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Snap ends off green beans and cook for 20 minutes.
Rinse and separate in bundles of 8-10 beans each.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around the bundle of beans and hold together with a toothpick. Place in dish, pour chicken broth over it and bake for 40 minutes on 350°.

title: french onion soup(crock-pot)
directions: Pour bouillon or stock in crock-pot.
Cook onions slowly in large skillet in butter.
Cover and let cook about 15 minutes. Uncover and add salt, sugar and flour.
Stir well.
Add to stock in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 hours. Before serving, top with grated cheese.
Recipe may be doubled for 5-quart model.

title: impossible cheese pie
directions: Place all ingredients (except coconut) in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pan.
Add coconut.
Bake in oven at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; cover and chill.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour the boiling water over the bran.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add creamed mixture, eggs and buttermilk to bran mixture.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in the "All-Bran."
Batter can be stored, covered, in the refrigerator for weeks.
Spoon mixture into desired number of muffin tins and bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix ingredients listed and set aside.

title: fred's dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Whip cream cheese.
Add sugar and fold in topping.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and cool.
Carefully spread over cheese filling.
Spoon cherry filling over this and then add more whipped topping.
Let cool for several hours before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Let boil for 2 minutes and 3 seconds.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Chill until hard.

title: banana bars
directions: Mix and pour into a 15 x 11 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Pour over first mixture and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until set.

title: tenderloin hot dish
directions: Slice tenderloin; dredge in flour, salt and pepper or seasoning salt.
Fry in oil in large deep frypan.
Simmer until done.
Add rest of ingredients and enough water to cover everything.
Use the can of soup to add water.
Over medium heat, cook until tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: strawberry sundae pie
directions: Crumble cookies (mix margarine and cookie crusts); press into bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread softened ice cream over crust. Cover and freeze until firm.
Just before serving, place fruit on top.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Melt jelly; allow to get cold.
Combine with other ingredients; chill before using.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Combine apple juice and cornstarch in saucepan; bring to boil stirring frequently.
Add butter and spices; mix well.
Stir in apples.
Spoon into pastry shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole dish
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and tomatoes in a pot until tender.
Boil fettucini macaroni in pot until tender.
Strain.
Put fettucini on plate; spread zucchini over macaroni.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar and salt.
Add other ground up ingredients.
Simmer about 20 minutes until changes color.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and mix alternately with the other ingredients.
Put in tube pan and bake at 275° for 4 hours.

title: ron's super burger
directions: Take 1 pound hamburger; throw on grill.
Butter bun.
Put hamburger on bun.
Enjoy!

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla; mix egg and milk into batter and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients into batter and mix thoroughly.
Place dough in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour.

title: gladys' beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook, covered, 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. In another bowl, combine sugar, eggs and oil. Beat well with spoon. Gradually add flour mixture to the creamed mixture. Add vanilla and gently fold in apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan or until knife is clean.

title: potato casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onion and drain.
Layer in casserole dish the hamburger, grated cheese and cans of soup mixed with milk.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° until cheese melts down, about 45 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Blend and pour through funnel into hot oil (375°) in cast-iron skillet.
Turn cake over to brown second side.

title: lemon lime chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, garlic and basil. Combine remaining ingredients except lemon and lime slices.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn and baste.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes more.
Garnish with fruit slices.
Bake at 400°. Calories:

title: favorite casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer hamburger, onion, green beans and soup in this order.
Salt and pepper to season.
Whip egg and mashed potatoes together.
Spread over soup.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press in tube pan.

title: peas ala maria(to be served with a roast)
directions: Wash and shell the peas.
Cook the pods in the water with the salt.
When done, discard the pods and cook rice until tender in the water.
Combine the butter, parsley and onion.
Heat to brown slightly.
Add peas and then slowly add the rice.
Cook together for five (5) minutes before serving.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and butter (1/2 cup). Beat with mixer until smooth. Spoon into greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.

title: rolled christmas cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Cream together first four ingredients. Mix together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.

title: creton
directions: Combine.
Cook over low heat about 2 hours, covered.
Blend with a mixer.
Let stand.
Take a spoon and take grease out.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into baking dish and bake in moderate oven (350).
Bake until pudding is firm in the middle.

title: party mix
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Melt butter with Worcestershire, pepper, Tabasco and garlic powder.
Pour over cereal.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
May add nuts now.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Stir often.
I also add cashew nuts and pecan halves (if I have them in the freezer).

title: reduced sodium potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Peel and cut into cubes; combine remaining ingredients and mix into potatoes.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Cook together slowly for 2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Top with mixture of last four ingredients.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: jewish pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Use tube pan, greased and floured.

title: seafood stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Arrange caps in lightly buttered shallow baking pan.
Brush with 7 tablespoons butter.
Chop stems. Add crabmeat, eggs, 1/4 cup breadcrumbs, mayonnaise, chives and lemon juice.
Spoon into mushroom caps.
Combine remaining butter and breadcrumbs.
Sprinkle over mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix all 3 cans of juices in punch bowl.
Add lemon juice and sherbet, if desired.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, covered, in enough lightly salted boiling water to cover for 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cool slightly.
Peel and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Halve slices.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in loaf pan and pour remainder of soup over top of the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crisp fried oysters
directions: Drain oysters, then place them, one at a time, into a plastic bag with the corn meal.
Shake bag to coat each oyster.
Place the coated oysters on a cookie sheet; freeze for 20 to 30 minutes.
Fry oysters, unthawed, in hot to medium oil until brown and crisp. Drain well on paper towels; salt to taste.
Keep oysters, warm, uncovered, on a warming tray.

title: wild western chili
directions: Brown beef, onions, chili powder (salt and pepper to taste). Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and 1 medium onion until onion is tender. Drain. Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil. Turn to simmer until liquid is almost absorbed.

title: black pepper bread twist
directions: In large bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients along with 1 cup of flour.
In one-quart saucepan, heat shortening and water until very warm.
Beat liquids into your dry mixed ingredients until just blended.
Stir in remaining flour, a little at a time, until you have a soft dough.
Knead dough 3 to 4 minutes.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out dough onto a lightly floured surface.
Cut dough into quarters, then cut each quarter into about 10 pieces.
With hands, roll each piece into a 12-inch long rope; twist 2 ropes loosely together.
Repeat until all dough is twisted.
Place bread sticks 1 inch apart on a cookie sheet.
Beat egg in a small bowl, then brush over each bread stick.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until bread sticks are browned and crisp.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients and form in two rolls.
Roll in paprika.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown onion (chopped) in butter.
Combine with other ingredients.
Pour in 1-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: delphine's cake dessert
directions: Bake cake in 11 x 18 x 1-inch cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly.
Mix pudding, using 1 3/4 cups milk.
Add cream cheese and mix thoroughly.
Spread over top of cake like frosting.
Add pineapple over pudding.
Spread Cool Whip like icing.
Sprinkle with generous coating of coconut.
Add cherries, if desired.

title: creamy-banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.

title: corn n' broccoli bake
directions: In a bowl, combine corn, broccoli, 1/4 c. saltines, egg, onion and pepper.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Combine butter and remaining saltines, sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Mix all other ingredients together except onion rings and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add to chicken in 2-quart dish and top with onion rings before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Make in A.M. and heat and serve at P.M.

title: pizza
directions: Mix yeast and water. Add salt, sugar and oil. Mix in flour. Work dough about 5 minutes. Let rest 10 minutes. Spread on pizza pans greased with Crisco. Let rise 1/2 hour. Spread sauce and toppings. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Add cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Step 1 (Morning):
Mix first 4 ingredients and let set all day at room temperature.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain pineapple.
Add bananas, strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into mold. Chill until set.
Spread sour cream over set jello.
Pour the rest of the gelatin mixture into mold.
Let stand for 2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place in a baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter.
Add olive oil, parsley, salt, lemon juice and garlic.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Add to butter mixture.
Shrimp will turn pink as they cook.
Cook rice (1 1/2 cups) until soft.
Combine shrimp mixture and rice into casserole and bake in oven for 8 minutes.
Put under broiler for 5 minutes to brown.
Eat and enjoy!

title: kentucky biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead a few times to make a soft dough.
Don't overknead or the biscuits will turn hard and dry.
Roll out to a 6 x 6-inch square.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
With knife cut dough into 12 even portions.
Do not separate.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off green peppers.
Remove seeds.
Wash and cook 5 minutes in boiling water (salted) deep enough to cover peppers. Drain and set aside.

title: mexican chicken rolls
directions: Pound split chicken breasts until thin.
Mix green chilies, olives and Monterey Jack cheese.
Divide equally on breasts.
Roll up tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Dip each roll in egg, then in chips to coat.
Brown lightly in hot oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix enchilada sauce, water and tomatoes and pour over chicken rolls.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in a shallow baking dish. Bake in a slow oven at about 350° until firm and brown.

title: chocolate chip toffee grahams
directions: Arrange graham cracker squares in a single layer on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine butter and sugar in saucepan over medium heat; stir constantly and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cinnamon and pecans.
Pour over crackers covering completely.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Cool in pan 5 minutes,.
Using a spatula, carefully remove to a wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Store in airtight container with wax paper between layers in refrigerator.

title: cheese-frosted cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower; remove leaves and cut out base but leave head in one piece.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 12 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Place cauliflower in a shallow, ungreased baking pan.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; spread over cauliflower.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: shaggy maple nut pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat well.
Add next 6 ingredients and beat.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° on middle rack just until custard is set.
Bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix together eggs, vinegar and sugar.
Cook in saucepan until thick.
Cool.
Stir in salad dressing and milk.

title: birdie tweats
directions: On stove top in saucepan combine melted fat and boiling water. Stir in quick cooking oats.
Remove from stove and add flour, sugar and peanut butter.
Stir all together.
Cool and stir until it forms a ball.
Refrigerate.
Put outside for the birds.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 6 tablespoons of juice. Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in 6 tablespoons of pineapple juice.
Add 1 cup cheese and pineapple. Mix well and spoon into greased 1-quart casserole dish. Combine melted margarine and crackers.
Spread on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: normandy sand cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg together.
Cream butter and sugar together, using electric mixer at medium speed, 5 minutes, or until thick and creamy.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with Madeira, beginning and ending with flour mixture; beat well after each addition.
Stir in lemon rind.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in pre-heated 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let cake cool in pan 5 minutes; turn out on rack to cool completely.
Dust with sifted confectioners sugar before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix milk, coconut, vanilla and pecans. Add 1 box sugar. Add as much of the second box of sugar as possible.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl combine salmon, crumbs, onion, butter and salt. Combine milk and egg and add to salmon mix.
Shape into a loaf on a shallow baking pan or in a 8x4x2 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Picante Sauce or creamed peas.

title: hot german-style potato salad
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes (do not peel); steam over small amount of water until tender.
Cool slightly.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan over high, heat vinegar, onions, sugar, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, cream oleo and both sugars.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy.
Add salad oil, lemon extract and peel.
Beat well until blended.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Grease cookie sheets, roll 1 teaspoon dough into a ball and flatten into a circle with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: sicilian tuna steaks
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute the onions in hot oil until soft but not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil, capers and olives.
Cover; simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add tuna steaks; poach, covered, for about 5 minutes on each side. Serve tuna with sauce spooned over it.
Serves 4.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, pickles, celery, paprika and celery seed.
Take the hard-boiled eggs and dice all but two.
Add to potatoes and mix.

title: vegetable strata
directions: Place bread cubes in bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside; in nonstick skillet, saute carrots, onions, zucchini and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in tomato. Cook 1 to 2 minutes more; spoon over bread cubes.
Blend egg substitute, milk and basil; pour over vegetables in pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with cheese during last 5 minutes of baking. Makes 6 servings. 85 calories; 149 mg. sodium; 2 grams fat per serving.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl; stir well.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 10-inch iron skillet; top with cheese.
Add remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake cornbread at 450° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken livers and rice
directions: Put oil, onion and livers in frying pan on medium flame (not too hot).
Cook until done to taste.
Wash the rice.
First let water, oil and salt come to a boil and add rice.
Use low fire and cover tightly for about 30 to 35 minutes, then mix with livers. Enjoy!!!

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Put all ingredients in a Ziploc freezer bag and knead until well mixed.
Roll into logs or balls.
Wrap in wax paper and twist ends.

title: english chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise last.
You may use more mayonnaise for desired consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple kraut pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops; fry until 1 tablespoon fat accumulates. Discard trimmings.
Brown chops on both sides in hot fat.
Remove chops.
Drain excess fat.
Combine kraut, applesauce, onion, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Pour in skillet.
Place chops on top and season.
Cover and simmer on stove top for 35 or 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serves 6.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift and add flour, cinnamon and soda.
Chop and add pecans, pineapple, cherries and raisins.
Drop from spoon on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° to 300° for approximately 20 minutes.
Wrap in tinfoil and store indefinitely.
Dates and citron may be added to this recipe if you like.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In large saucepan, heat Italian dressing.
Cook mushrooms over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice. Remove mushrooms with dressing to large, shallow baking dish. Cover and marinate in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, 4 hours or overnight.
Makes about 4 cups of mushrooms.

title: chicken and gravy
directions: Fry chicken in margarine.
Place artichoke hearts in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top.

title: tuna cheese ball(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Drain liquid from tuna.
Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
You may roll in chopped pecans.
Chill at least one hour. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, dissolve bouillon cube and water.
Add broccoli and carrot.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain.
In another saucepan, melt butter and slowly stir in flour.
Continue stirring while gradually adding the milk.
Stir in the cheese, soup, onion flakes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add the broccoli mixture to the white sauce mixture and cook over medium to low heat until the soup is desired thickness.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine veggies, soup, half of the cheese, sour cream, pepper and half of the onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: ranch boneless chicken breasts
directions: Wash and dry breasts.
Dip in Ranch dressing.
Completely cover with breadcrumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: norwegian reubens
directions: Top 6 slices rye bread with onions, dividing evenly.
Combine sauerkraut, apples and caraway seed.
Spoon over onions.
Top with pastrami, cheese and turkey.
Cover with remaining slices of bread.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet over low heat. Grill sandwiches until golden on both sides, turning once, adding additional butter as needed.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: microwave mexican chicken kiev
directions: Pound raw chicken with mallet to flatten.
In small bowl, beat together butter and cheese spread.
Mix in onion, salt, m.s.g. and chiles.
Place a portion of mixture at one end of each chicken piece and roll up, tucking in ends to completely enclose filling. Fasten rolls with toothpicks.
Dip each roll in melted butter to cover, then coat with mixture of crackers and taco seasoning mix.

title: chilaquiles(mexican lasagna)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and garlic in a large skillet over medium-high heat until onions are tender.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, kidney beans and chilies.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally until juices begin to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Spread half the sauce in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch casserole.
Top with half the tortillas, half the sour cream, sauce and half the cheese.
Complete with remaining tortillas, sour cream, sauce and finally, cheese.
Bake 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a 13-inch tube pan with butter.
Sprinkle raisins and walnuts along the bottom.
Roll frozen dinner rolls in cinnamon to coat.
Place on top of the raisins and walnuts (completely line the bottom of the pan with rolls).
Sprinkle dry vanilla pudding on the top of the rolls.
Next, sprinkle brown sugar over the pudding.
Drizzle melted butter over the brown sugar.
Cover pan with a tea towel and let sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn rolls from pan immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken, soup and sour cream.
Place in baking dish.
Top with poppy seed and crackers.
Pour melted margarine over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double lime cooler
directions: Spoon sherbet into bowl and stir to soften.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into glasses and serve cold. Yield:
4 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion and potatoes in 6 cups water.
Add vegetables and soups.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: energy salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Add 1/4 to 1/3 cup Light Dressing.
Toss well.
The tomatoes and cucumbers are important because their water content will help digest the more fibrous greens.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: double bake blue cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes 20 minutes or until tender in microwave; remove top of potato with knife.
Scoop out potato; in electric mixture, mix potato inside and rest of ingredients.
Re-fill potato skin with filling; bake 15 minutes in oven at 400°.

title: almond sugar cookies(easy to make.)
directions: Mix
all
above
ingredients,
except almonds, in large bowl with
a
fork.
Knead
dough a few times.
Half dough and knead again.
Roll
up in wax paper the size of a half dollar. Chill for 1
1/2 hours.
Pat out on an ungreased cookie sheet and put
an almond in middle of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dump in pineapple, pie filling and sprinkle cake mix over top.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with nutmeats and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from pan and cook celery and onions in broth.
Add soups (undiluted), tomatoes and seasonings.
Cut chicken in pieces
and add to soup mixture.
Line large baking pan (9 x 13-inch) with Doritos.
Pour chicken mixture over chips
and top with grated cheese.
Bake in 350°
oven until cheese is melted.

title: scalloped hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole dish and top with 1/2
c. grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: thelma's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: french burnt peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until moisture evaporates.
Turn out onto a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with vegetable oil or something similar.
Roast at 275° for 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: soft pimento spread
directions: Grate cheese.
Heat milk and cheese but do not boil to melt. Add pimento, pickle relish, mayonnaise and salt.
Cool.
Will keep in refrigerator for 10 days.

title: oven baked doughnuts
directions: Let first 3 ingredients rise 10 minutes or so.
Scald milk and add Crisco, 1/2 cup white sugar and salt.
Let the mixture cool and add eggs.
Last add flour and nutmeg.
Add yeast to scalded milk mixture.
Add egg mixture and mashed potatoes.
Add flour last of all.
Let rise 2 hours until doubled and punch down.
Let rise 10 minutes more and roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut out doughnuts. Place doughnuts on cookie sheet.
Let rise until double their size. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: ghoul-ade
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: strawberry orange punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix together just before you are ready to serve.

title: texas cheese dip
directions: In heavy pot, brown the meats and onion until cooked and finely chopped.
Drain excess fat.
Add cubes of Velveeta until all cheese is melted.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Serve in a chafing dish with Triscuits crackers or tortilla chips. Serves 30 to 40.

title: shelia's never fail fudge
directions: Mix first three ingredients well. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil exactly 8 minutes. Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, pecans and vanilla. Mix well and pour into a buttered cookie sheet. Cool and cut into squares. Makes a lot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread cubes, meat and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
Spoon off any excess grease while cooking.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding mix in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. Batter will be stiff.

title: spinach-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables 5 minutes.
Drain extremely well.
Mix next 5 ingredients with vegetables.
Put in greased casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook fryer in boiling water with 1/2 tablespoon dry onion, stalk celery and 2 teaspoons of salt. Not too much water.
(Use rich broth to cook rice.) Cook chicken until tender.
Let cool until skin can be removed and cut in bite-size pieces. Steam broccoli until just tender.
Drain and place in bottom of casserole.
Add chicken.

title: fruit sparkler(jell-o salad)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and remaining ingredients. Can either be placed in a 6-cup ring mold or in a square cake pan.

title: baked stuffed shrimp # 2
directions: Peel, clean and butterfly the shrimp and place them in a shallow casserole.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over the shrimp.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: Place graham cracker on a paper napkin to keep cracker crisp. Top with chocolate and marshmallow.
Microwave on High until marshmallow puffs, about 20 to 30 seconds.
Top with second half of cracker.
Let stand 1 minute so chocolate melts.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add buttermilk and eggs, stirring well. Carefully drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil (370°); cook only a few at a time, turning once. Fry 3 minutes or until hush puppies are golden brown. Drain well on paper towels. Makes about 3 doz.

title: creamy mushroom scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup/milk mixture and onions.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Put potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour mushroom mixture over potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: eight can casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart casserole, mix everything except onion rings.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on onion rings. Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old timey lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and croutons.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with remaining cheese and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: snappy joes
directions: In a large skillet, cook the beef, green pepper and onion for 5 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, barbecue sauce and coleslaw mix.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Spoon into buns or tortillas or over each baked potato.

title: easy tangy barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Mix spices; rub into beef. Place seasoned meat in shallow glass baking dish. Top with sliced onion. Pour over barbecue sauce and beer mixed together. Cover. Roast 3 hours or until fork-tender. Remove meat. Let stand 15 minutes. Halve meat. Shred 1/2 into another shallow covered dish. Pour over 1/2 sauce. Return to oven. Shred other half. Add to sauce in original pan. Heat through. Serve on rolls. Prep: 25 minutes. Crock-Pot: 10 to 12 hours. Oven: 325° for 3 hours.

title: goulash
directions: Saute onion in butter until yellow.
Add meat but do not brown.
Add rest of ingredients, using enough water so meat is half covered.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumble flour, lard and salt together.
Add cold water. Chill.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each one.
Sift flour, add to sugar, butter and eggs mixture.
Mix until smoothed.
Add lemon flavor and 7-Up.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage and onion together; drain.
Mix with sour cream, cream cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins, chopped nuts, soup and shortening.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and mash squash.
Add onion.
Combine layer of squash and butter.
Add cracker crumbs, grated cheese with other ingredients and layer on squash.
Add layers until all used.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions and drain. Place in dish.
Add cheese and soup.
Stir to mix.
Cover with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Combine all; mix well.
Put in airtight jar.
Add 2 to 4 spoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: sausage biscuits (balls)
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add sausage and mix thoroughly. Change to mixing bowl.
Add flour.
Make into small balls or biscuit size.
Bake in preheated oven 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts or roll into logs and wrap in wax paper as icebox cookies. Chill and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: hawaiian ham sandwich
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix with ground ham, brown sugar and cloves.

title: "mother and child" in the garden
directions: Saute all fresh vegetables and chicken until coated.
Beat eggs with soy sauce and pour over vegetables and stir.
Cook completely.

title: dump cake
directions: *Yellow or white cake mixes may be used, if preferred.

title: coquille san jan
directions: Wash scallops and drain thoroughly.
Simmer scallops in wine for about 5 to 6 minutes, turning occasionally.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Set aside scallops.
Melt butter and add scallions, mushrooms and parsley.
Saute.
Stir in flour until blended.
Then add and blend the reserved liquid and cream, simmering to create a sauce.
Add scallops to sauce.
Continue simmering and blending for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: kwanzaa jollof rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large pot. Brown chicken.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook on medium heat 5 to 10 minutes. Saute shrimp in remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in a small skillet. Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a large pan.
Add carrots, green beans and peas. Cook about 5 minutes.
Drain vegetables, reserving 3 cups cooking liquid.

Add to chicken in stockpot along with shrimp, tomatoes, salt, black pepper, cayenne and thyme. Reduce heat to low. Simmer 5 minutes. Combine rice and tomato paste in bowl. Stir until rice is coated. Stir into large pot.
Add small amounts of water as needed to prevent sticking. Cook about 20 minutes or until chicken, vegetables and rice are tender.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet; drain.
Add rice, seasoned salt and oregano.
In 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer sliced zucchini, meat mixture and cottage cheese.
Next spread can of mushroom soup and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: baklava
directions: Cut the pastry sheets in halves and roll out to 9 x 6-inches on floured board; melt butter.
Roughly chop nuts and mix with cinnamon.
Put pastry sheet on damp baking tray, brush with melted butter and cover with 3 more sheets pastry, brushing butter between each layer.
Spoon nut mixture over pastry, leaving 3/4-inch border.
Cover with remaining 4 sheets pastry, buttering each layer.
Trim off pastry to make neat rectangle.
Knock up edges.
Score top in 6, then score each section in half diagonally.
Bake at 425° for 7 to 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, bake for 20 minutes more.
Warm honey and lemon juice in pan.
Spoon over hot pastry and let soak, serve warm.
Hope you'll try this.
It's served all over the Middle East as is Lamb Tayine. Bon appetit.

title: chocolate surprise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and chocolate chips until smooth.
Add nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shells and vegetables italiano
directions: Prepare shells and cheese as directed on package.
Toss shells and cheese with remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately or chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Heat water and oleo to a boil. Stir in flour all at once. Beat until mixture forms a ball.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: colossal cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside. Combine flour and sugar; add milk and almond extract.
Stir until blended.
Spoon batter over butter; do not stir.

title: potato and pea soup
directions: Cut potatoes into small chunks, add package of peas with pieces of onion, cut small.
Add water.
Bring to boil.
When potatoes are tender, drain off 1/2 to 2/3 of water.
Add milk to cover ingredients.
Heat to boiling, adding salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Serves well with hot muffins or biscuits. Amount of ingredients can be increased or decreased according to preference.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake 1/2 of the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: beef sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Knead daily for the next 3 days.
On the fourth day, shape into 5 small loaves. Place on a cookie sheet; bake for 10 hours at 200°.
Turn after 5 hours.
Wrap and refrigerate or freeze.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together and shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown meatballs in 1/4 cup fat or salad oil. Remove the meat and stir into the fat the next 4 ingredients.
Add milk and boiling water.
Stir and simmer and return meatballs into the gravy.

title: streamlined white bread
directions: In a bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour.
Add shortening, salt, sugar and half the flour to yeast.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Add remaining flour.
Blend in with a spoon.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise in a warm place until double, about 30 minutes.

title: quick crab quiche
directions: Drain
and
flake
the	crab.
Beat
together the eggs, cream, onions, wine, salt, dry mustard and tarragon.
Put crab and cheese in the pie shell.
Pour the balance of the ingredients
over the crab and cheese.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for
to
35 minutes or until the knife inserted in center, comes
out
clean. Let
stand	for
5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: creamy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken with onion on all sides in margarine in a large skillet. Add tomatoes, green peppers, milk and seasonings; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover. Simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Uncover. Continue cooking 10 minutes. Remove chicken to platter; keep warm. Stir Velveeta cheese into skillet until melted. Serve over chicken.

title: jewel candy
directions: Measure white sugar, corn syrup and water on scale (3 pounds). Mix together in saucepan and boil to scant 300° (hard-crack stage). Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients. Transfer to ungreased 2 qt. baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until heated through. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: shirley's hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; set aside.
Slice potatoes and arrange in layers with onions.
Salt layers.
Put meat on top.
Pour tomato soup over entire casserole. Place peppers on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
(If you are in a hurry, you can reduce your baking time to about 20 minutes by boiling potatoes and onions for a few minutes before putting in casserole.)
Use a 1 1/2-quart size casserole dish. Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until over done.

title: orange chess pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until firm).

title: million dollar pies
directions: Mix well and pour in cooled pie crusts.
Chill before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut or break cauliflower into small pieces.
Cut black olives into thin circles.	Dice green onions (including tops) and mushrooms.	Mix together; toss with Zesty dressing.
Cover and let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: individual fruit strudels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Carefully unroll phyllo pastry.
Work on a cool surface.
Cover remaining phyllo with a damp cloth. Take 1 sheet of pastry at a time and brush lightly with melted margarine.
Cover with another sheet.
Repeat for 2 more sheets, brushing with butter in between.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter and mix with pretzels.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and save broth.
Mix soups and can of the chicken broth.
Tear chicken into bite size chunks and add to soup mixture.
Heat soup mixture and pour into casserole mix.
Top casserole with stuffing mixture.
Press down into soup mixture. Heat in oven at 350° until hot or crumbs are brown.

title: yellow punch
directions: Add required water to orange juice and lemonade.
Add 7-Up just before serving.
Serves 25.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients except ice cubes.
Add ice cubes and blend until crushed.
Serve them.

title: party rye pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage; drain.
Melt in Velveeta.
Add oregano.
Spread on bread.
Put in oven for 10 minutes at 350°, then serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute chicken, onions, garlic and parsley until chicken is completely cooked.
Sprinkle generously with teriyaki sauce.
Add 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth. Heat until warm.
Mix remaining 1/2 can of chicken broth with cornstarch; add to chicken and stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small pieces and mix with sour cream and soup.
Mix well
and
put
into casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Pour
melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Boil chicken; pull off bone.
Saute chicken, onion and garlic in margarine until chicken is lightly browned.
Stir in cornstarch and cook 1 minute.
Add broth, carrot, lemon juice and salt; bring to a full boil.
Stir in pea pods, parsley and rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until egg mixture is done like custard.

title: golden harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 36 muffin cups with paper cup or grease bottoms only.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a 4-quart bowl, combine all dry ingredients and walnuts; mix well.
Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir just until moistened.
Fill lined cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Immediately remove from pans.
Makes 36.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos; set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: mom's lobster bisque
directions: Heat the soups (undiluted) together with the cream and bring to just under a boil.
Add the seafood and heat through.
Add the sherry just before serving and heat for another minute.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash.
Mix 1/2 package of the stuffing with all ingredients, reserving 1/2 package for topping.
Place squash mixture in a casserole (2-quart) dish that has been greased and sprinkle the remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot cheesy beef dip
directions: Saute pecans in butter 3 to 5 minutes, then drain on paper towel.
Set aside.
Place dried beef in blender. Chop finely and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and milk in a medium mixing bowl; beat on medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Stir in beef, green peppers, onion and garlic, mixing well.
Add white pepper and sour cream.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve dip hot with assorted crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple and let it stand a 1/2 hour. Bring slowly to a boil and cook for 12 minutes.
After it starts boiling, remove from heat.
Stir in the dry gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water for 30 to 35 minutes or until fork-tender.
Remove from heat, cool, peel and slice 1 inch
thick.
Place sliced apples, salt, maple syrup and butter in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes or until almost tender. Place half the potato slices in a layer in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon half the apple mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layering potatoes and apple mixture.
Put crumbs on top and bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler (cook slow). Blend in milk and stir over hot water or low heat until thick (about 15 minutes).
Blend small amount of mix in the beaten eggs, then pour back into rest of custard.
Cook, stirring constantly for 4 or 5 minutes.
Chill the mix well (important for smooth ice cream).
Add vanilla and cream.
Pour in gallon freezer.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter or olive oil.
Add mushroom soup, salt and pepper; stir until blended. Add chicken and mushrooms; simmer for a few minutes.
Grease 1-quart casserole and pour in mixture; sprinkle with noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Follow instructions on Rice-A-Roni, but only use 1/4 cup water.
Add rice to hamburger, onion and egg.
Make tablespoon size meatballs.
Pan fry in oil; turn and brown until done.
Make gravy and pour over meatballs.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Brown bacon and chopped onion. Add cabbage, apples, salt, pepper, sugar, vinegar and caraway seeds. Cook until cabbage is soft, about 2 hours, on medium-low heat. Add additional sugar and vinegar if necessary. If the cabbage becomes dry, add water. The cabbage will have a sweet and sour taste.

title: spinach dip
directions: Make up dressing mixing with 1 cup mayo and milk.
Set aside. Cook chopped spinach; cool.
Mix 1 cup mayo, sour cream, lemon juice and seasoned salt.
Add to Ranch dressing.
Stir in cooled spinach.

title: honey-grilled tenderloins
directions: Trim fat from tenderloins.
Butterfly tenderloins by making lengthwise cut in each, cutting to within 1/4-inch of other side. Place in a shallow container or large, heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bag.
Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic; pour over tenderloins. Cover or seal.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove tenderloins from marinade, discard marinade. Combine brown sugar, honey and oil in a small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium-hot coals (305° to 400°).
Place tenderloins on rack and brush with honey mixture.
Cook 20 minutes or until choice of tenderness, turning once and basting frequently with honey mixture.

title: date coconut balls
directions: Melt margarine in heavy saucepan or skillet.
Add sugar, egg and dates.
Cook 2 minutes after it starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Let cool.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in Kellogg's Pep and butterscotch chips.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: easy sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice on slant.
Rinse out jar and repack slices.
Boil next ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Pour over pickle slices.
Refrigerate.
Cheaper to use your own spices: whole cloves, allspice, celery seed and cinnamon (whatever you have).

title: apple dew dessert
directions: Cut up each apple to make 8 long slices for a total of 16 slices. Cook in a boiler the margarine and sugar until dissolved and add vanilla flavoring. Roll 1 slice of apple in each crescent roll. Place in an 11 x 13-inch pan all 16 rolls with apples. Cover them with butter and sugar mixture. Then add Mountain Dew over all the mixture. Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Take foil off and bake another 10 to 15 minutes, until rolls begin to brown. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: toast pizza
directions: Toast bread.
Put pizza sauce on toasted bread.
Sprinkle cheese; microwave for 30 seconds.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine the first 9 ingredients; mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Saute in butter in a 3-quart Dutch oven until browned; drain meat well and set aside.
Blend flour into hot pan drippings, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add consomme and water; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in sour cream. Reduce heat and heat gently.
Add meatballs; heat thoroughly. Serve over hot cooked rice, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Add margarine, spices and enough juice to fluff potatoes. Form into balls around marshmallows and roll balls in corn flakes. Place in greased dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Crust:	Melt
water
and margarine together.
Add flour to form a ball.
Mix
in
eggs, one at a time.
Spread mixture on a floured and
greased
cookie
sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Crust will look lumpy when done.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Mix the sour cream, taco sauce, tomato sauce and enchilada mix with the meat.
Layer the meat sauce, tortillas and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, gradually add to softened cream cheese.
Mix well until blended.
Stir in juices and orange rind.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir and taste. May need extra salt.
If not moist enough, add some more mayonnaise.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Rinse in warm water and return to pot.
Add package of cheese, margarine and evaporated milk.
Mix. Beat egg in the sweet milk and add to macaroni.
Grate Colby cheese and add half of cheese to macaroni mixture.
Fold in.
Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle remainder of cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until slightly brown.

title: pesto genovese
directions: Blend oil, cheese, pine nuts, salt, pepper and garlic in a blender until smooth.
To this mixture add the basil and blend until smooth.
Freeze in 1/2 cup portions.

title: no rolling pie crust
directions: Blend flour with salt.
Blend oil with milk.
Mix together with fork and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Use as an unbaked pie shell or if recipe calls for a baked crust, bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit punch by jane
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; add ginger ale just prior to serving.
Serve over crushed ice with a sprig of mint.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put oil and vinegar in blender.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.

title: clam chowder
directions: Simmer (do not boil) the first 8 ingredients in a covered saucepan for 5 minutes.
In the meantime, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in a saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook only until slightly thickened.
Add remaining butter, clam mixture and cream.
Garnish with paprika.
Sprinkle crumbled pretzels over soup.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: bagels
directions: Combine water, sugar, yeast and salt.
Add about 5 cups flour to the ingredients until stiff, then beat vigorously.
It is important to knead dough for a long time.
Let it rise once.
Then shape and roll out twelve ropes.
At this time, add raisins, broiled onions, etc.
Wet ends to join together.
Let rise until doubled.

title: beef roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over roast.
Cook in oven at 400° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: dried beef cheese balls
directions: Chop
dried beef in blender.
Mix other ingredients in a bowl; add
dried
beef,
reserving
enough
to coat the cheese balls. Shape
into 2 small or 1 large cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: tuna patties
directions: Drain tuna; put into mixing bowl.
Add egg and onions; mix well.
Crush a handful of crackers into bowl.
Mix, then make patties.
Put oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown on each side.

title: jerusalem chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and paprika; set aside.
Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray; heat skillet.
Add chicken and cook for 5 minutes or until browned, turning once. Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Arrange artichoke hearts around chicken; set aside.

title: chocolate stuff
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar together.
Mix with margarine and press into dish.

title: moist marble cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add oil, vinegar, vanilla and cold water.
Mix and set aside.
Mix in another bowl the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix both batters as for a marble cake.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Frost when cool and freeze.
Freezing gives the cake extra moistness.
Remove cake from freezer several hours before serving.

title: creamed chicken in crock-pot
directions: Put all in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours.
Serve over biscuits or rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean and prepare peppers.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes. Take out and drain.
In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned slightly and veggies tender.
Drain off fat. Add tomatoes and uncooked rice, water, salt and Worcestershire sauce and a dash of pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 18 minutes or until rice is tender.
Take off heat and stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy turkey and pasta primavera
directions: In 4 quart saucepan, cook pasta according to directions.
Add broccoli, carrots, onions and pepper strips the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Add pasta/vegetable mixture and turkey over low heat.
Heat through, stirring frequently.
Makes 5 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine, soup, cheese, onion, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Melt 1 or 2 tablespoons margarine and mix with corn flakes. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: diet coke jello
directions: Heat to boil juice from cherries and pineapple. Add jello, Coke and pineapple. Mix well. Refrigerate in large bowl.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Mix macaroni with all the remaining ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Makes 5 cups.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Mix sugars, milk and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until mixture starts to thicken, then turn into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash and core apples.
Put on and cook (peeling and all). After tender, run through colander.
Add ingredients.
Cook in heavy pan.
After apples get to cooking good, turn down and cook for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and make sure you boil your seals and rims before placing on jars.
Good on toast or English muffins.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Crumble and mix with cheese.
Spread in bottom of 7 1/2 x 12-inch flat baking dish.
Fry and drain bacon or sausage.
Cut in small pieces.
Sprinkle over bread and cheese. Beat eggs, milk, seasonings and mustard.
Pour over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until firm in center.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: miracle chocolate cake(no milk, no eggs, no butter and no baking powder.)
directions: Sift first five ingredients into mixing bowl.
Make three depressions in dry ingredients with a large spoon.
Pour vanilla into one, salad oil into another and vinegar in the third.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
When cool, frost with favorite icing. Serve with ice cream or chocolate sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes one 9-inch or 2 regular pies.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; lay on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put chicken on next; mix next 3 ingredients and pour on chicken.
Sprinkle cheese, then top with crumbs.
Makes 8 servings.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef-zucchini casserole
directions: Cut off ends of zucchini/squash and cook whole in lightly salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute onion in butter (2 tablespoons), add beef and brown lightly.
Pour off fat.
Stir in crumbs, salt, pepper and oregano.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add chopped meat.
Reheat for 45 minutes on low heat.

title: texas size chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked
broccoli
in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Put
cooked
meat over broccoli.
Sprinkle with several dashes
of Worcestershire
sauce,
a
thin
layer of Parmesan cheese and
a few dashes of lemon juice.
Top with mayonnaise, sour cream
and chicken soup.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar and butter together and pat down well in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in slow oven (270°) for 10 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Grease crock-pot with oleo and then let it melt inside.
Mix all remaining ingredients into pot.
Cook 4 hours on low.

title: eight layer salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer salad in order beginning with lettuce. Spread mayonnaise over top of green peas as you would spread a meringue.
Spread to edges of bowl.
(This layer must be sealed completely.)
Sprinkle over mayonnaise 2 tablespoons of sugar, grated cheese and bacon.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate from 4 to 24 hours before serving.
When serving, be careful not to scoop off the top but dig down in.

title: bartlett's shrimp scampi
directions: Saute butter, oil, parsley and garlic for 1 minute.
Add shrimp and cook for another 2 minutes.
Add wine, salt and pepper. Cook on medium to low heat for 5 more minutes.
Serve over linguine.
Serves 4.

title: swedish tea cakes or snowball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Cool slightly; roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely; roll again in powdered sugar.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: chocolate banana split
directions: Pour milk into a medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon pudding evenly into 4 dessert dishes. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Halve and split bananas just before serving.
Place 2 pieces in each dish. Top each serving with 2 tablespoons whipped topping. Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: hunters stew
directions: Brown meat in fat in heavy Dutch oven.
Add garlic and onion and saute.
Add salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate.
Stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover and cook until tender, about 25 minutes.

title: quick easy fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with foil (butter foil).
Combine sugar and milk in a medium size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to boiling.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; beat in chocolate and marshmallows with wooden spoon.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Pour into prepared pan and let stand until cool and firm.

title: low-fat spinach stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until firm but tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix drained spinach, cottage cheese, garlic, lemon juice, Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Stir in the beaten egg.
Stuff the shells with the mixture and place in a baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Top shells with spaghetti sauce and finally, the cheese.
Bake at 350° until all is hot and the cheese melted, about 20 minutes.

title: applesauce treat
directions: Pour applesauce into a saucepan and add remaining ingredients. Heat through over medium heat until butter melts and mixture is hot.
This can be served at breakfast as well as lunch and dinner.

title: deluxe steak casserole
directions: Coat steak with flour and paprika.
Brown in oil in skillet. Add salt, pepper and 1 cup water.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Place in casserole.
Heat soup in pan drippings, blending in 3/4 cup water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Combine with meat mixture and onions; mix well.
Top with celery seed.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: curried tomatoes
directions: Wash, dry and quarter the tomatoes.
Heat oil in a skillet; saute onions for 5 minutes.
Mix in garlic, salt and curry powder; add tomatoes and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: easy pecan coffee cake
directions: Butter a large Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan, then arrange roll dough over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Melt margarine, then add brown sugar, continuing to cook until it starts to boil.
Pour over rolls.
Let stand on counter overnight, uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn onto a plate immediately.

title: aloha dip
directions: In a bowl, stir together macaroons, sugar and sour cream. Chill several hours to soften macaroon pieces.
Do not stir again. Place chilled dip in center of a large platter.
Arrange fruit and berries of your choice around the dip.
Sprinkle fruit and berries with Kirsch or brandy, if desired.

title: coffee marshmallow creme
directions: Melt marshmallows and coffee together in top of double boiler until smooth.
Cool, then add whipped cream.
Stir well.
Pour into serving glasses.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry. Stir together with other ingredients. Blend well. Refrigerate 2 hours. Stir before serving. Serve with Hawaiian bread or crackers.

title: texas tamale dinner
