directions: Place all ingredients in an ovenproof dish. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Remember to place Doritos on bottom of dish. Top with lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.
Microwave for 10 to 15 minutes on High. Serves 4.

title: mexican delight
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain grease. Mix soups, sour cream and diced tomatoes. Add meat and mix all together.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add cocktail sauce before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Slice sausage links into round chips; place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Dice onion; layer with potatoes.
Potatoes should be cut up scallop style.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
May garnish with cheese.

title: slow cooker black bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours (or on low 8 to 10 hours).

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain. Add all other ingredients and mix with beater. Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook first two ingredients in crock-pot until tender.
When meat is very tender, remove from pot.
Take out onion and bone. Shred meat with fork until very fine.
Return to crock-pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook overnight at lowest temperature of crock-pot.

title: oriental cabbage
directions: Layer in large skillet.
Cut in a half stick butter on top; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook slow for 12 to 15 minutes (no water).
You can change to vegetables in season.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Halve chicken breasts and place in a glass baking dish. Season with a little salt and pepper.
Mix the Catalina dressing and cranberry sauce together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake about 1 hour at 375° or until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Put half of mixture in baking dish.
Layer chicken.
Pour half the broth over chicken. Mix sour cream and soup together.
Spread over chicken.
Add rest of stuffing mix, then spoon remaining broth on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Melt butter.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Add melted butter and beaten eggs.

title: mandarin mist
directions: Drain pineapple juice in bowl and add jello.
Mix and stir. Then add Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and cottage cheese. Refrigerate.

title: gingered shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp under running water and devein.
Heat water to boiling.
Add 2 tablespoons salt and shrimp.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Place shrimp in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie shell for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: beef or lamb
directions: Clean the meat and cut into pieces.
Boil with little salt and some of the chopped onions until tender.
Fry the meat.
Put a saucepan on medium heat with the vegetable oil when hot.
Add flour and stir until lightly brown.
Add the rest of the onions, green peppers and tomato sauce and mix well for 5 minutes.
Add the meat stock and the meat and let it simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve with potatoes, rice or ripe plantains.

title: banana-honey muffins
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat in honey and bananas.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture, beating just until blended.
Stir in oats, raisins or nuts.
Fill greased muffin tin or baking cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 375°.
Delicious when warmed for a brunch or anytime treat!

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, mayonnaise, cheese, onion, salt and pepper. Lightly spray baking dish with Pam cooking spray.
Place mixture in baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cast-iron skillet with iron handle is preferred since it can be used on range top and go directly into oven.
Saute onion in small amount of oil.
Add beans, sugar and mustard.
Stir slowly over medium heat until well mixed.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
May be baked longer if sauce is too thin.
Amounts of onion, sugar and mustard may be adjusted to suit your taste.

title: avocado with lemon yogurt dressing
directions: Halve the avocado.
Remove seed and peel.
Combine all ingredients in food processor until smooth.
Cover and chill before serving.
Use with fresh lettuce.
(Can also be used with cold chicken or seafood.)

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in shallow 1-quart casserole or baking dish.
Add raisins.
Sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Mixture should be coarse and crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over the apples.
Cover lightly with foil and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer until the top is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, dates, sugar and shortening in bowl.
Pour boiling water over this.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices and stir into first mixture.
Add cherries and walnuts or pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in angel food pan (greased).

title: hurry-up pie
directions: Drain
pineapple juice.
Add lemon to milk and beat.
Stir in pineapple; fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until thick.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Drain salmon; retain liquid.
Combine the first 3 ingredients. Mix baking powder in 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.

title: polenta
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and sprinkle in cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Polenta is cooked when it begins to leave the sides of the saucepan.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream powdered sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put into 2 cooked pie shells. Refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and flour.
Then melt butter; add to mixture and then add coconut.
Cook about 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Cook at 350°.

title: "apple cranberry crisp"
directions: Arrange sliced apples in baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Spoon cranberry sauce over apples. Stir together oatmeal, flour and brown sugar; cut in butter. Sprinkle over cranberry sauce. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crispy chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix Bisquick and pepper in a plastic bag.
Stir chicken in eggs; remove and place in bag.
Shake to coat with mix, then remove.
Put 1 tablespoon oil in wok.
Stir-fry carrots 2 minutes. Add pepper and stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Remove veggies.
Add remaining oil, then stir-fry chicken until golden brown.
Add carrots, peppers and onions.
Stir-fry 2 minutes, then add pineapple.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corned beef
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Spread mustard on top of beef. Sprinkle pepper and parsley flakes over the mustard.
In this country a corned beef brisket usually comes with it's spices and juices in the package.
Add the spices and juices from corned beef package.
Place meat in Dutch oven.
Add vinegar and just enough water to almost cover meat, but don't put in so much water that you cover the mustard and the spice topping.
Heat just to boiling and then reduce heat, cover pan and simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Quarter the potatoes and chop the onion and add both to pan.
Cover and return to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for another 15 minutes.
Core the cabbage, cut it into wedges and add to pan.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes more until veggies are tender.
Place meat and veggies on a platter and season with salt and pepper.

title: butter muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients just until blended. Spoon batter into lightly greased muffin pans, filling to top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown chopped sausages and stir in onions.
Saute for 2 minutes, stirring often.
Drain grease.
Stir in chili sauce and jelly.
Simmer for 30 minutes

title: quick turkey hash
directions: Melt shortening in pan.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in turkey, potatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add milk a little at a time.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom pastry; flute edges or prepare a braided crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely. Store in the refrigerator.

title: cold cabbage slaw
directions: Sprinkle sugar over the above mixture.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla. Mix well. Add butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first five ingredients in order given; divide 1/2 of mixture between the three pie shells.
Warm fudge topping enough so it can be drizzled over top of peanut butter mixture.
Divide remaining peanut butter mixture and spread on top of fudge sauce. Drizzle remaining fudge sauce over three pies.
Cover and freeze. Serves 16 to 24.
Keeps well in freezer 3 to 4 weeks.

title: manicotti villa santa maria
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In
large bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, prosciutto (if desired), eggs, parsley, pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Stuff manicotti with cheese mixture; arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon pasta sauce over manicotti; top with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Bake 40 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hank's potato salad
directions: Cook peeled, quartered potatoes in lightly salted boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bring ingredients to boil stirring constantly, boil 1 minute. Pour over vanilla wafers.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream. Can be reheated in microwave.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oil, butter, sugars and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Make into balls. Dip in colored sugar and flatten with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: super casserole
directions: Place 2 slices of buttered bread (quartered) in bottom of 9-inch buttered pan.
Mix celery, onion, green pepper and mayonnaise.
Add shrimp, fish or crab.
Pour over bread.
Place 2 remaining quartered slices of bread on top.
Blend eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with soup (undiluted).
Bake another 30 minutes.
Add grated cheese and brown.
Serve immediately.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Spread on dish or pizza pan.
Drizzle with sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Arrange apples around dip.
Apples can be sliced ahead of time if marinated in pineapple juice to prevent turning brown.

title: tomato-ginger soup
directions: Puree onion and ginger in food processor.
Transfer to bowl. Puree tomatoes in food processor; set aside.
Melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion puree and cook 4 minutes to blend flavors, stirring frequently.
Add tomato puree, consomme, 1 tablespoon of sugar, salt and pepper; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Add cream.
Reduce heat and simmer until reduced to 3 1/2 cups, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Taste and add more sugar, if desired.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix together
and
bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased sheet.

title: low-fat tartar slaw
directions: Whisk all ingredients, except cabbage and carrots.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Toss to mix and coat.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat together with sugar until creamy. Fold in all remaining ingredients.
Put in loaf pan and freeze. Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: bread dough clay
directions: Mix flour and salt in large bowl.
Slowly add water while mixing until uniformly moistened.
Remove and knead 6 to 10 minutes (on well floured surface).
Roll out.
Cut or shape dough as desired.
Allow to air dry or bake in moderate oven at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush with egg whites before baking for a golden brown color.
Paint and seal with clear sealer.

title: natalie's chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken; debone and dice.
In large soup pan, strain broth.
Add bouillon cubes (1 cube per cup of broth).
(I add water plus more bouillon, 1 cube per cup of water.) Add in chicken and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for several hours.
Towards the last hour, add noodles and vegetables. Cook until noodles are done.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; blend in flour, then add milk slowly, stirring to keep smooth.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens and boils.
Stir some of hot sauce into egg yolks, then return to pan, stirring until smooth.

title: california walnut pie
directions: Melt brown sugar, flour, Karo, margarine and salt in microwavable bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla while stirring constantly so eggs don't cook.
Add walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until filling is set.

title: wrapped olives
directions: Mix well. Wrap olives completely in dough.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashion southern tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add well beaten egg, milk and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Roll out to about 1/4-inch thickness on lightly floured board. Cut out with round cutter and bake on greased baking sheet in a preheated 375° oven.

title: salad gardeniere
directions: Put oil, lemon juice, chopped garlic, Parmesan cheese and salt in a jar.
Mix and let stand for 1 hour.

title: maple layer cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add the maple syrup; stir in the eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, ginger and salt.
Add to the syrup mixture.
Stir in the hot water, nuts and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool in the pans for 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from the pans.
When cool, frost with Maple Frosting (recipe follows).
Makes 1 double layer cake.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Place sausage in electric skillet. Add the tomatoes.
Heat until hot.
Add cheese in chunks and melt. Serve hot with chips.

title: blueberry topping
directions: Heat blueberries with water, sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water (cold).
Stir in blueberry mixture and cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Can be used as pie filling or topping for cheese cake.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease or Pam baking pan.
Put coconut and pecans in pan.
Mix cake mix by directions; pour in pan.

title: instant cherry cream pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk in blender until smooth. Pour into baked pie shell.
When firm, spoon pie filling on top.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add dressing tossing lightly.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, crumble bacon over top.
Serves 6.

title: summer casserole
directions: Slice, steam and drain squash.
Add carrot, pimento, onion and chicken soup.
Mix (stuffing mix) sour cream, butter and stuffing mix.
Add 1/2 this mix to casserole.
Sprinkle other half over top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cut stew meat into 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute beef in oil until meat is brown.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Empty beans into colander and rinse bean juice off beans.
Add beans and heat.

title: pineapple carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water to cover for 10 minutes until tender; drain.
Drain liquid from pineapple; set pineapple aside. Combine juices with cornstarch, salt and cinnamon in medium saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yields 8 servings.

title: molho verde cru(portuguese sauce for fish)
directions: Cut garlic and rub the inside of small mixing bowl with cut sides, pressing to crush slightly (discard remaining garlic). Combine remaining ingredients in the bowl.
Cover and chill. Serve over cooked fish fillets or cooked seafood.
Makes about 1/2 cup sauce.

title: paula's pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread Pillsbury rolls on 18-inch cookie sheet.
Press together so all holes are together.
This is to form your crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: beef-and-vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice across grain into 3 x 1/4-inch strips.
Set aside.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain juice from pears, peaches and pineapple.
Save to make 2 cups.
Discard juice from grapes and oranges.
Cut pears and peaches into bite sizes.
Mix all fruit into a large glass serving bowl (I use a small punch bowl).
Mix pudding and 2 cups of saved juice.
Heat to a boil, cool.
Pour fruit and mix well.
Then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: maple french toast
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except bread and butter.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
In large, greased skillet, cook bread in butter until golden.
Serve warm with Maple Butter and pure maple syrup.

title: carrot tuna salad
directions: Mix tuna, onion, carrot, celery and mayonnaise.
This can be done the day before serving.
Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes.
Serve on a lettuce leaf garnished as desired.

title: war cake(loaves)
directions: Place the 9 ingredients in large pan and boil, then let cool. Sift the 3 remaining ingredients, then add to cool mixture.
Place batter into well-greased loaf pans.
The mixture makes 2 loaves. Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: In large pan, mix the sugar with the water; bring to boil for one minute; let cool. Mix in orange juice and cherries. Put in large containers and freeze. When ready to serve, place frozen mixture in a large punch bowl and pour ginger ale over. This needs to be put together about 30 minutes before serving. Frozen mixture will keep for a long time in the freezer.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 12-inch pan about 25 minutes.

title: medley
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add soups and heat. Add noodles.
Place in casserole. Cook in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour until noodles are done.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: marvelous meatless casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley.

title: banana pudding
directions: With an electric mixer (I use a whisk), beat until milk and pudding are creamy. Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip until smooth. Layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers, as many layers as you want.

title: morales hot bean-cheese dip
directions: Bring peppers to boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and let cool. Place in blender with tomato sauce and blend well.
In saucepan, saute this with onions for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and beans. Stir until cheese is melted and mixed well.
Great as a dip for nachos or Doritos.

title: cherries in the clouds
directions: Mix last five ingredients with electric mixer or whisk until smooth.

title: italian chicken
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, heat oil on medium heat.
Dip chicken in beaten egg.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil over medium heat for 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Lay chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with cheese, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° to melt cheese and heat spaghetti sauce.
Serve over noodles cooked according to package directions.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put Jell-O in a Pyrex dish.
Put the package of marshmallows on top of Jell-O.
Pour the boiling water on the Jell-O and marshmallows.
Stir.
Put in refrigerator until almost jelled. Then stir in the crushed pineapple and whipped cream.
Add as many pecans as you like.
Return to refrigerator.

title: honey celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add vinegar and honey.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add lemon juice and oil very slowly, beating constantly until mixture thickens.
This dressing becomes very thick when put in refrigerator.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir until reaches a spreading consistency.
Spread on cake.
Cut into squares.

title: no fail microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a 2-quart casserole. Cook 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. (If you use a candy thermometer, the reading should be 260°.)

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar; beat in water, oil and egg.
Cover bowl; refrigerate until ready to bake.
Grease muffin tins and fill all the way full.
Bake at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Melt margarine in a nonstick skillet.
Peel potatoes and grate.
Mix ingredients together.
Fry.
(If they don't stay together when frying, you need more flour.)
Very good!

title: picante chicken chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large pan until tender.
Stir in chicken; cook until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir constantly.
Sprinkle sage, cumin and salt over chicken.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in picante sauce, beans, vermouth and bay leaf.
Boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in pepper and tomato; continue to simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Discard bay leaf.
Ladle into bowls.
Top with picante sauce. Serves 4.

title: fried cakes
directions: Roll out 1/3-inch thickness and cut with doughnut cutter. Fry doughnuts and holes in hot lard until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit in a large bowl.
Add orange juice concentrate; toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: fruit and cheese salad
directions: Mix together and chill for an hour.

title: southerland pralines
directions: Combine sugar, milk, Karo, oleo and soda in pan.
Place over medium heat, stirring gently until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft boil stage at 238° on candy thermometer and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased casserole.
Cook, covered, 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Return to oven 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies as per instructions on box.
Prick holes in baked brownies and pour Kahlua over top.
Prepare mousse as per instructions on box; break candy bars into pieces.
Layer ingredients in glass dish in following order: brownie, mousse, Cool Whip and candy bars.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush half of strawberries, leave rest whole.
Make syrup of water, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and salt.
Add crushed berries and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Place whole berries in pie shell.
Let cooked filling cool a little and pour over whole berries.
Chill and serve.
Top with spoon of Cool Whip.

title: peachy nut bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and set aside.
Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Beat eggs in with sugar and Crisco.
Stir in buttermilk/sour cream and peaches (mashed and drained).
Then add the ingredients that were first set aside.
Mix until moistened.
Fold in orange rind, cut up cherries and nuts.
Turn batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color.
Mix
sugar, cornstarch, butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Arrange half of asparagus in a buttered 8-inch square dish. Combine peas, soup, mushrooms and cheese, blending well.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over asparagus.
Repeat layers.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil and shredded zucchini squash well. Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and chopped nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, mixed with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into custard cups and set in a pan of water (about 1 inch).
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on your oven.
Check after 30 minutes.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Mix together and place in casserole.
Can make ahead.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: granny's enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Drain excess fat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans. Add chopped pepper.
Heat.
Layer tortillas and the beef mixture in a deep greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Garnish with chopped tomato and chopped green pepper.
I serve it with sour cream also.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash cream cheese with fork; add crumbles of drained shrimp, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with fork, then add mayonnaise until right consistency.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: crust chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush chicken breasts with mustard and set aside.
In a large shallow dish, mix together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, onion, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs mixture.
Place in large lightly greased pan, meaty side up.
Drizzle chicken with melted butter.
Bake uncovered 50 minutes or until tender.
Arrange in a dish.
Top with yogurt or sour cream.

title: chicken and sausage cassoulet
directions: In a small saucepan combine the carrots, onion and water. Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer covered 5 minutes.
Transfer to a 3 1/2 or 4 quart crockery cooker.
Stir in tomato paste, wine and seasonings.
Add beans.

title: stewed tomato soup
directions: Cook the onions and garlic until a little brown.
Put in the tomatoes and a little water.
Add carrots (beans green), celery and any other kind of vegetable you have.
Cover with water.
Add a bouillon cube or two to give a good taste.
Let cook and then eat it.

title: candy coated peanuts
directions: Mix sugar, water and peanuts.
Boil and stir until all water is gone.
Then put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in oven on 325° for about 20 minutes.
This finishes cooking peanuts.

title: clam casserole
directions: Mix well and bake in a 375° oven in an ungreased casserole dish or bread pan for 45 minutes.

title: st. ann's summer luncheon turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Spread each slice of bread with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise. Arrange slices in well-buttered baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Cover with turkey or chicken.
Cook and stir mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add water chestnuts and heat through.
Sprinkle over turkey or chicken.
Cut cheese slices diagonally in half; arrange in 2 rows (points overlapping in same direction) on mushrooms and water chestnuts.

title: german rocks
directions: Cream the butter. Add sugar gradually.
Beat in eggs (well beaten first). Dissolve soda in water. Add to mixture with sifted flour. Drop on greased sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° depending on oven. If electric, 350°.
Fruit should be floured before added. If dough is runny, add more flour.
Cookies should not be flat.

title: tiny tim bars
directions: Combine and pour on top.
Bake 35 minutes longer at 325°. Cool.
Cut into small bars.

title: streusel topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sweet potatoes and syrup until blended.
Spoon in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumb.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle over the sweet potatoes. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
A very yummy dish.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cook Time:
40 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients; pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until crust is brown on edges.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a small skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender. Remove from heat.
In a bowl, combine onion mixture, sour cream, half of the cheese, milk and chilies.
Add hominy; mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger with onions and bell pepper; drain.
In large pot, empty 2 cans of chili beans, can of stewed tomatoes and water. Add hamburger meat, jalapenos and chili spice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving.

title: robyn's dip
directions: Mix to dip consistency.
Serve with crackers.
Best made a day ahead.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix, cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.

title: toll house oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together flour, salt and soda.
Blend sugars, vanilla and water.
Add egg; mix well.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate bits.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: easy large cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large oblong Pyrex dish. In small saucepan, heat together fruit with 1 pint water or cherry juice and 1 cup sugar until sugar dissolves.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Pour over melted margarine; do not stir. Spoon fruit and juice over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, onion and pepper together.
Lightly grease dish. Crush chips.
Place half of the chips in dish, then put half the soup, half the chicken mixture and add the cheese. Repeat with other half.
Be sure cheese ends up on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ham swirls
directions: Place ham slice on plate.
Spread cream cheese on ham.
Place a small pickle or green onion in the middle on top of the cream cheese.
Roll up and cut into pinwheels.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Let cool some.
Add the Mountain Dew.
When cool, add the pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let cool in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan until set.
Prepare the lemon pudding according to instructions.
Put on top of jello. Put Dream Whip on top of the pudding.

title: wild rice chicken dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Put in casserole. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow instructions on cake mix.
Pour half of the cake mix into a 9 x 12 pan and bake 15 minutes.
Melt butter, caramels and milk and pour over cake.
Then pour remainder of cake mix over cake and bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In 2-quart saucepan combine brown sugar, sugar, flour and salt.
Add water, butter, corn syrup and vanilla.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Arrange potatoes in baking dish.
Pour sugar mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pipi kaula
directions: Cut meat 1/2 x 1 x 6-inches long.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add meat.
Let soak 20 minutes, then turn.
Soak for 1 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Place strips of beef on 1/4-inch mesh wire pipi kaula screened drying box.
Place box in sun for 8 hours.
Take drying beef indoors at sundown.

title: egg jelly(passed down 5 generations in dudley family)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and about one teaspoon nutmeg.
Pour into skillet where you have bacon
or sausage drippings and stir constantly until mixture boils or is frothy.
Remove from stove and serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: speedy quiche
directions: Saute ham, onion and green pepper in oil until vegetables are tender.
Spoon into lightly greased 10-inch deep dish pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: spinach salad
directions: Pull the stems off the spinach and wash the leaves.
Pat dry. Tear the spinach into pieces.
Cut the peppers in strips and add it to the spinach.
Cook bacon and crumble into salad.
Shake the vinegar, salt and pepper in a jar.
Add oil and shake again. Crumble the Blue cheese and add it to the dressing.
Pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Beat with mixer.
Add vanilla, nuts or peanut butter.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Chill, cut and serve.

title: apple dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling in oblong Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans over mixture.
Sprinkle cake mix over pecans and apples. Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans over cake mixture.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, then buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Sift flour together with baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into the other mixture.
Add nuts last and stir in.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
During this time, preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Remove to wire rack.
Serve warm or cold.

title: hot mustard
directions: Place mustard and vinegar in glass bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add sugar and eggs.
Cook on low temperature, stirring while cooking, until thick.
This is good served with ham.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Place margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High until melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in parsley, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Cover.
Microwave at High until shrimp is pink (do not overcook or shrimp will become tough) 3 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes, stirring twice.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken-cabbage casserole
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat chicken (reserve flour mixture).
In large skillet, heat oil over medium high heat; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove.
Saute onion in fat until golden brown and tender, then stir in caraway seed and reserved flour mixture until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and bouillon; cook and stir until thickened.
Spread cabbage in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over; top with chicken.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until cabbage is tender. Serves 6.

title: war cake
directions: Let first 9 ingredients boil 5 minutes.
Let cool 8 minutes. Mix soda in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add salt and flour.
Mix altogether and bake in large pans.

title: easy pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add Cool Whip when pudding is thick. Mix in cereal.
Put in refrigerator and let it sit for a short while.
Serves 6.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Melt macaroni in skillet.
Saute onion until lightly browned. Add green beans, turkey and pimento.
Stir in soup, sour cream and macaroni.
Toss lightly.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, sour cream and Cool Whip in bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour mixture into graham crust and chill for 2 hours.
Immediately before serving, cover with cherry pie filling.

title: roasted chestnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Score the chestnut halfway around the nut.
This will prevent the chestnut from exploding.
Place chestnuts in ovenproof skillet (cast-iron is best) over high heat on the stove top.
Roll the nuts by shaking the pan until all are toasted.
Then put the skillet in the oven and cook until the shells split or about 10 minutes.
Peel the chestnuts and enjoy as an appetizer, a snack or a garnish.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef, green pepper, onion and celery salt in frying pan until beef turns brown.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with mushroom soup, then layer with grated cheese, then cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
This dish freezes well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding pecans last.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake pie 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes.
Filling will be firm and crusty with pecans on top when done.

title: cocoa fudge candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Cook over low heat. Do not stir until it comes to a boil or it will become gritty.
When the candy forms a soft ball when tested in cold water, it is done. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter and butter.
Let cool for about 10 minutes.
Beat to a spreading consistency. Spread on dish or pan greased with butter.

title: crackles
directions: *Good results with chocolate chip, orange, butter pecan, spice, German chocolate and marble.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil the raisins, margarine, sugar and 2 cups cold water for 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole(my sister paula's recipe)
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Grease an oblong casserole dish (Pam spray or Crisco).
Pour all of the ingredients in, except bread crumbs or
Pepperidge Farm stuffing and 1/2 stick margarine.
Top with bread crumbs or stuffing and dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Delicious!!

title: taco junk
directions: Fry ground beef and drain the grease.
Add taco seasoning and refried beans.
Mix well. Crush half of the chips in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or glass baking dish. Add your ground beef mixture on top of chips. Smooth Cheddar cheese soup on top of the mixture.
Add the rest of the chips to the top.
Bake in oven at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Put in refrigerator in an airtight container for anywhere from 4 to 48 hours.
The longer refrigerated, the more flavor!
Grill.

title: easy pumpkin nut pie
directions: Prepare nut cookie crust.
Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly in large bowl; stir in pumpkin, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt, cloves, ginger and nutmeg until smooth; gradually stir in evaporated milk.
Pour into crust.
Cover edge with 2 to 3-inch strips of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes longer.
Cool pie completely.

title: fruity citrus slush
directions: In a blender container combine banana, pineapple juice, sugar and orange juice.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 large containers.
Stir in the 1 1/2 cups water and the lemon juice.
Apply seal and freeze for 6 hours or until firm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until done and remove from bone.
Cook broccoli until done and arrange in well-greased, flat casserole dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, juice, mayonnaise and curry. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icing for angel food cake
directions: Combine these ingredients, adding about 1/3 of the confectioners sugar at first.
Alternate adding milk and remaining sugar for icing.
Beat well.
